column2: "Ba-gawk," Chica says. She eyes the empty birthday plates sadly.
column3: “咯-咯，”奇卡说。她忧伤地望着空荡荡的生日盘子。

column2: "Ba-gawk?" Chica says as she takes the birthday cake. Tears come to her eyes.
column3: “咯-咯？”奇卡一边说着，一边拿起了生日蛋糕。她的眼里已经泛起了泪花。

column2: "He bounced the moon, spelled his name in the stars, and ran through the snow with the silent hunter."
column3: “他弹跳过月亮，用星星拼出自己的名字，还和那个寂静的猎人在雪地中奔跑。”
“救救我们！”他们低声呼喊。

column2: "My dollies are all broken!" She cries. "I cannot fix them. So I will fix you!"
column3: “我的洋娃娃全坏了！”她哭喊道，“我修不好她们。所以我要修理你！”

column2: "My name is Sun," the old woman says. "Come with me." She then motions you over to her workbench.
column3: “我的名字叫太阳。”老妇人这样说道，“跟我来吧。”说罢，她招手示意你来到她的工作台旁。

column2: "No ticket!" Big Top says as he grabs you and pulls your head off.
column3: “没票可不行！”蛛顶票王说着，一把揪住你，把你的脑袋扯了下来。

column2: "Now you will get your reward. Use this to bring him back. It's all in your hands now."
column3: “现在轮到你领取报酬了。用这个把他带回来，一切就看你的了。”

column2: "Opening Day" Snow Globe. A wonderful day with all of us at Fall Fest.
column3: “开幕日”雪景球。那是咱们大家在秋祭的美好日子。

column2: "Thank you!" they whisper. "Big Top is gone! We're free!"
column3: “谢谢你！”他们低声欢呼，“蛛顶票王消失了！我们重获自由！”
“洞穴在等你呢。”

column2: "This is a very special, magical mask. The Moon will now think you are the Baby Owl."
column3: “这是件非常特别又充满魔力的面具。现在，月亮会把你当成小猫头鹰。”

column2: "Where is my owl?" You ask the Oak Tree. He says the owl is gone, which makes you sad.
column3: “我的猫头鹰去哪儿了？”你向橡树发问。他只是说猫头鹰已经离开了，这让你满心失落。

column2: "You fixed my dollies!" the Nurse says. "My work is done!" She then leaves the Doll Hospital, happy forever more.
column3: “你修好了我的娃娃！”护士欢呼道，“我的任务完成了！”然后她永远幸福地离开了洋娃娃医院。

column2: "You have found my presents. You have completed my tasks."
column3: “你找到了我的礼物，也完成了我的任务。”

column2: "You have your reward and your sacrifice. The Cave awaits you now."
column3: “你已获得奖励，也献出了牺牲。现在，洞穴正等待着你。”

column2: "You must fix these three masks. They will give you a great reward."
column3: “你必须修好这三张面具。只要完成，你就会收获厚礼。”

column2: "You rebuilt yourself, but now you are split in two. Moon and Sun, Destruction and Life."
column3: “你拼凑好了自己，但如今却一分为二—月亮和太阳，毁灭与新生。”

column2: A Deadeye Roxy Rodeo Hat. You wore this until it fell apart. Everyone loves Roxy.
column3: 一顶死眼洛克西牛仔帽。你戴这顶帽子直到它完全破损。所有人都喜欢洛克西。

column2: A Golden Rabbit Mask. There’s a slash across its face that needs to be repaired.
column3: 一只金色兔子面具，脸上有道伤痕亟待修复。

column2: A Grand Prize Trophy. Stolen in the night from the Moon's bedroom.
column3: 一座大奖奖杯，夜里从月亮的卧室被盗走。

column2: A Halloween Mask. This can fool anybody!
column3: 一张万圣节面具，连最精明的人也能被骗倒！

column2: A Hedgehog Halloween Mask! This can fool anybody!
column3: 一只刺猬万圣节面具，能瞒过任何人！

column2: A Starbright Night Light. It takes the firelight and burns forever.
column3: 星光小夜灯。它承接篝火的光芒，点燃后永不熄灭。

column2: A Starbright Night Light. It takes the firelight and burns forever.
column3: 星光小夜灯。它承接篝火的光芒，点燃后永不熄灭。

column2: A broken statue stands in the center of a huge central chamber. Passages lead in all four directions.
column3: 一尊破碎的雕像矗立在巨大的中央大厅。四个通道分别通往不同方向。

column2: A forest path leads deeper into the night next to an oak tree.
column3: 林间小径沿着一棵橡树，通向更深邃的黑夜。

column2: A forest path leads deeper into the night, but it's blocked by a Gator who is trying to eat a Baby Owl.
column3: 林间小径本可通往夜色深处，却被一只正准备吃小猫头鹰的鳄鱼挡住了。

column2: A forest path leads deeper into the night. A very happy Baby Owl hoots and flies around your head.
column3: 林间小径通向更深夜色。一只极其开心的小猫头鹰在你头顶边叫边飞。

column2: A giant loom. Surprisingly it has survived the fire.
column3: 一台庞大的织布机。不知怎的，它竟在大火中幸存下来。

column2: A large blue crystal in the center of the room. It looks like there’s something inside...
column3: 房间中央矗立着一块巨大的蓝色水晶，里面好像有什么东西……

column2: A lizard, a squirrel, and a snake are having a tea party. Nothing unusual.
column3: 一只蜥蜴、一只松鼠和一条蛇正围坐品茶，一切都平平常常。

column2: A ruined workshop deep underground. Broken statues litter the ground. Another south passage leads deeper into the caves.
column3: 一间废弃已久的工坊，地上满是坏掉的雕像。向南还有一条通道通往更深的洞穴。

column2: A statue of the Baby Owl. You will bring him back, no matter the cost.
column3: 一尊小猫头鹰的雕像。无论付出多大代价，你都要把它带回来。

column2: A strange, tall waterfall coming out of a stone cistern. There's an area behind it.
column3: 一道奇高的奇异瀑布从石制蓄水池中奔涌而下。瀑布后面似乎藏着什么地方。

column2: A thick, muddy pond with a large boulder next to it.
column3: 一个厚重泥泞的池塘，旁边耸立着一块大巨石。

column2:
A toy phone rings. 
A child cries softly on the other end. 
"He never sees me..."
column3:
玩具电话响了。
电话那头有个孩子在低声哭泣。
“他永远看不见我……”

column2: An ancient pirate ship lays stranded inside a giant cave. How did it get in here?
column3: 一艘古老的海盗船搁浅在巨大洞穴深处。它到底是怎么进来的？

column2: Ancient ruins. The west passage heads towards the cave entrance, and the south passage leads deeper.
column3: 古老的遗迹。西侧通道通向洞口，南侧通往更深的洞穴。
询问小猫头鹰

column2: Big Top is deactivated, but with a smile on his face. He has found peace.
column3: 蛛顶票王已经停机，但脸上带着微笑。他终于安息了。

column2: Big Top looms in front of the Prize Wheel. Mannequins stand in silence around him.
column3: 蛛顶票王伫立在奖品转盘前。假人们静静地围在他身边。

column2: Big Top puts your head back on. "YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED HERE!" he screams as he pushes you out of the world.
column3: 蛛顶票王把你的头安回去。“你不许来这里！”他尖叫着将你推出这个世界。

column2: Big Top then shuts down, silent forever more.
column3: 随后，蛛顶票王也永远沉默下去。

column2: Big top takes the ticket. "This is the one. This is where the Sun left, leaving them behind."
column3: 蛛顶票王收下票。“就是这张。这里是太阳离开的地方，留下了他们。”

column2: Blackened and burned mannequins. You can hear them weeping.
column3: 乌黑焦灼的假人，你能听见他们在哭泣。

column2: The Baby Owl coos and flutters his wings.
column3: 小猫头鹰咕咕叫着，扑扇翅膀。

column2: The Baby Owl coos and rubs against your hand.
column3: 小猫头鹰发出咕咕声，蹭着你的手。

column2: The Baby Owl looks at you with love in its eyes as it eats a worm.
column3: 小猫头鹰吃虫时满怀爱意地看着你。

column2: The Baby Own chirps happily. He then rubs against you and coos.
column3: 小猫头鹰愉快地唧唧叫，然后扑向你，发出咕咕声。

column2: The Bear Mask is missing his Bowtie. You'll need to find it.
column3: 熊面具少了领结，你得去找一个。

column2: The Bear jumps off the swing and eats you right up!
column3: 熊从秋千上一跃而下，一口把你吃掉！

column2: The Bear on the porch growls and you back off.
column3: 门廊上的熊低吼一声，你吓得往后退。
衣橱打开了
衣橱打不开

column2: The Doll Hospital is dark and silent now. The dolls are fixed and happy.
column3: 娃娃医院里一片黑暗安静，娃娃们都修好了，也很开心。

column2: The Foxy Mask is missing one of its eyes. You'll need to find more to fix it.
column3: 狐狸面具少了一只眼睛，你得再去找一只来修好它。

column2: The Gator snaps at you. You back off.
column3: 鳄鱼猛地咬向你，你连忙后退。

column2: The Glitched Permission is yours. Use it wisely.
column3: 你得到了损坏的权限，请谨慎使用。

column2: The Moon Statue sings and is reborn! It glows and glows until you know nothing but white...
column3: 月亮雕像唱着歌重获新生！它不断发出耀眼的光芒，直到你的视野被纯白吞没……

column2: The Moon comes out of the darkness of the cave. "Not now. I'm too busy! Back to Bed!" Everything fades to black.
column3: 月亮从洞穴的黑暗中现身。“现在不行，我太忙了！快回床上！”世界随之陷入黑暗。

column2: The Moon comes out of the darkness of the cave. "Not now. I'm too busy! Back to Bed!" Everything fades to black.
column3: 月亮从洞穴深处走了出来。“现在可不行，我很忙！赶紧回床上！”一切顿时黑暗下来。

column2: The Moon grabs you from Big Top's clutches. "YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED HERE!" he screams as he pushes you out of the world.
column3: 月亮将你从蛛顶票王的魔爪中夺走。“你不准待在这里！”他怒吼着，一把把你推出了这个世界。

column2: The Moon grabs you from Chica's beak. "YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED HERE!" he screams as he pushes you out of the world.
column3: 月亮把你从奇卡的喙中拉开。“你不允许留在这里！”他大声怒吼，硬是将你赶出了这个世界。

column2: The Moon grabs you from Dollie's clutches. "YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED HERE!" he screams as he pushes you out of the world.
column3: 月亮突然扯你脱离多莉的魔爪。“你不能待在这里！”他一边大叫，一边把你推离了这个世界。

column2: The Moon grabs you from Jackie's clutches. "YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED HERE!" he screams as the world fades to black.
column3: 月亮把你从杰基的手中夺走。“你不该待在这里！”他愤怒地喊着，世界瞬间归于黑暗。

column2: The Moon picks you up off the floor.  "YOU'RE NOT ALLOWED HERE!" he screams as he pushes you out of the world.
column3: 月亮把你从地板上捡起。“你不能呆在这里！”他怒吼着，把你硬推出了这个世界。

column2: The Moon pulls you out of the bear's stomach. "What are you doing? Back to Bed!" he screams. Everything fades to black.
column3: 月亮把你从熊的肚子里拽出来。“你在干嘛？快回床上！”他大喊着，一切随即陷入黑暗。

column2: The Moon saves you from the poison. "What were you thinking? Back to Bed!" he screams. Everything fades to black.
column3: 月亮救你脱离了毒液。“你到底在想什么？回床上！”他喝道，黑暗无声降临。

column2: The Moon stops you from exiting the house. "Back to bed!" He screams as he grabs you and everything fades to black.
column3: 月亮拦住你离开房子。“回床上去！”他一边大叫一边抓住你，整个世界变得漆黑。

column2: The Moon takes one look at your Owl Mask and begins to cry. You enter the Cave.
column3: 月亮看到你的猫头鹰面具，眼泪夺眶而出。你随即步入洞穴。

column2: The Oak Tree groans. It seems to be in pain.
column3: 橡树发出一声低低的呻吟，仿佛正承受剧痛。

column2: The Oak Tree groans. It seems to be in pain. It looks like a knife is sticking out of the side.
column3: 橡树痛苦地呻吟着，树身侧面竟插着一把刀。

column2: The Old Woman gives you a Baby Owl Mask.
column3: 老妇人递给你一只小猫头鹰面具。

column2: The Old Woman smiles. "The Baby Owl flew away."
column3: 老妇人微微一笑：“小猫头鹰飞走了。”

column2: The Old Woman smiles. "Time for you to meet your fate, dear child."
column3: 老妇人带着暖意微笑：“孩子，该是你面对命运的时候了。”

column2: The Old Woman stops you. "That is not the way now."
column3: 老妇人拦住你：“现在不能走这条路。”

column2: The Sun appears. She comes in from the sky and smiles.
column3: 太阳现身。她自天空中降临，满脸微笑。

column2: The Toy Pirate Ship is empty. Where's its captain?
column3: 玩具海盗船空荡荡的。它的船长去哪儿了？

column2: The Toy Soldiers stand at attention. They don't even crack a smile.
column3: 玩具士兵笔直地站得整整齐齐，一个笑容都没有。

column2: The Toy Soldiers stare at you. They know what you've done.
column3: 玩具士兵一动不动地盯着你，他们已经知道你犯下的事情。

column2: The Vacuum Pet. His greatest success and his greatest failure.
column3: 吸尘器宠物。他既是主人的最大成功，也是他最深的失败。

column2: The animal masks are warped and strangely... human looking.
column3: 动物面具已经扭曲，奇怪地带有几分人类的模样。

column2: The animal masks stare at you and growl.
column3: 那些动物面具盯着你，发出低沉的咆哮。

column2: The animatronics watch you with glowing orange eyes.
column3: 那些机械玩偶用橘色的眼睛，静静地注视着你。

column2: The book has changed. "The end comes from the beginning. To sleep the tiger, you must complete the story."
column3: 书的内容发生了变化：“终结自始而生。要让猛虎入睡，必须讲完整个故事。”

column2: The branch is too thick. You can't break it.
column3: 树枝太粗壮，你怎么使劲也折不断。

column2: The cave entrance. There's a passage leading to the east.
column3: 洞穴的入口处，有一条小道通向东边。
箱子里空空如也。

column2: The deactivated Big Top stares at nothing, while the mannequins watch in silence.  A prize wheel stands ready to spin.
column3: 已停摆的蛛顶票王空洞地凝视虚无，假人们静默旁观。旁边的奖品转盘，等待着被你旋转。

column2: The dial reset. You'll have to start over.
column3: 旋钮已归零，你只能从头再来一次。

column2: The door is barred from the other side.
column3: 门被从里面闩上了，无法打开。

column2: The fish laugh at you and swim away.
column3: 鱼儿嘻笑着游开了，仿佛在戏弄你。

column2: The man has a Bowtie that looks weirdly out of place. Like someone had stuck one on the statue.
column3: 这个男人佩戴着一只格外突兀的蝴蝶结，仿佛有人硬生生地给雕像添上的。
鸟巢里什么也没有。
鸟巢里空荡荡的。

column2: The oven is very cold. Nothing is cooking inside.
column3: 烤箱冰冷，里面没有任何食物在烹饪。

column2: The pirate ship is broken and unstable. It's unsafe to walk on.
column3: 那艘海盗船破损不堪、摇摇欲坠，已经无法安全行走。

column2: The ruins of a quaint little seamstress shop. A large loom sits in the corner surrounded by mannequins.
column3: 一间古色古香的小裁缝铺已成废墟。角落里，一台巨大的织布机依偎在一群假人之间。

column2: The seamstress shop has been burned to the ground.
column3: 这家裁缝铺已被彻底焚毁，化为焦土。

column2: The soup tastes strange, like plums and nutmeg. The world spins, and the last thing you see is the Moon above...
column3: 这汤喝起来古怪，隐约有李子和肉豆蔻的味道。世界开始天旋地转，你视野中的最后一幕是头顶上的月亮……

column2: The statue has a left arm and a right arm, but no head.
column3: 这座雕像有左臂和右臂，但没有头部。

column2: The statue has a left arm, but no head or right arm.
column3: 这座雕像有左臂，但没有头和右臂。

column2: The statue has a moon head and a left arm, but no right arm.
column3: 这座雕像有一个月亮形的头和左臂，但没有右臂。

column2: The statue has a moon head and a right arm, but no left arm.
column3: 这座雕像有一个月亮形的头和右臂，但没有左臂。

column2: The statue has a moon head, but no arms.
column3: 这座雕像只有一个月亮形的头，没有任何手臂。

column2: The statue has a right arm, but no head or left arm.
column3: 这座雕像有右臂，但没有头和左臂。

column2: The statue has two brightly colored legs and a torso, but no arms or head.
column3: 这座雕像有两条色彩鲜艳的腿和一个躯干，但没有手臂和头。

column2: The stove is very hot. Something is cooking... smells like chicken.
column3: 炉子非常烫。有什么正在煮……闻起来像鸡肉的味道。

column2: The terrain is too rough to cross without help.
column3: 地势太崎岖，没有帮助根本过不去。

column2: The thing pulls you to the Moon, who screams "Back to Bed!" Everything fades to black.
column3: 那东西把你拉向月亮，月亮尖叫着：“回去睡觉！”眼前一切陷入黑暗。
玩具箱里什么也没有。

column2:
The wall carving has four arrows. 
Left, Right, Right, and Left.
column3:
墙上的雕刻刻着四个箭头。
左、右、右、左。
窗户上了锁。

column2: The window is open. It's really cold outside.
column3: 窗户开着，外面冷得厉害。
工作台上什么都没有。

column2: There is a Foxy Puppet steering the ship.
column3: 有一只狐狸木偶正在掌舵。

column2: There is a Sewing Kit near the loom.
column3: 织布机旁放着一个缝纫工具包。

column2: There is a Toy Hammer on the workbench.
column3: 工作台上有一把玩具锤。

column2: There is a crate of Rainy Day Boots in the corner.
column3: 角落里有一箱雨天靴。

column2: There is a golden Fishing Net draped over the side of the ship.
column3: 船的一侧搭着一张金色的渔网。

column2: There is a soft click as the chest opens!
column3: 箱子开启时，传来一声轻微的咔哒响！

column2: There is a square record nailed to the three. "Fredbear's Singing Show". Our favorite restaurant.
column3: 一张方形唱片被钉在树上，上面写着“弗雷德熊歌唱秀”。那是我们最喜欢的餐厅。

column2: There is a strange machine in the closet.
column3: 壁橱里摆着一台奇怪的机器。

column2: There is nothing in the closet anymore. The thing is gone.
column3: 壁橱里已经空了，那个东西消失不见。

column2: There is nothing inside the tree stump.
column3: 树桩里什么都没有。

column2: There's a letter on the desk. "Dear Moon, can you bring back the Sun?"
column3: 桌上有封信：“亲爱的月亮，你能让太阳回来吗？”

column2: There's a very steep path leading into the mountains next to a sign and a hollow stump.
column3: 一条很陡的山路通向高处，小路旁立着一块牌子和一根空心树桩。
这里只有这些，没有其他东西了。

column2: There's nothing there, but there is something sticky down the sides.
column3: 那里没有什么，但两边摸起来有些黏糊糊的。

column2: There's something at the bottom of the pool, but you can't reach it.
column3: 池子底下好像有点什么东西，但你就是够不到。

column2: These are ancient ruins of what was once a happy home. A fire has blackened the walls.
column3: 这里是曾经温馨家园的古老遗迹，如今墙壁被大火熏黑。

column2: These cystals are all misshapen. They look like pieces made from other crystals.
column3: 这些水晶形状奇怪，像是由碎裂的其他水晶拼凑而成。

column2: This rock is beautiful on the outside, but dark things move under the surface, like worms through mud.
column3: 这块石头表面美丽，然而里面黑暗的东西在蠕动，像泥里的虫子。

column2: This used to be a grand underground city. Now it's nothing but dust and silence.

column3: 你在树林里偶遇一间破旧的小屋。门廊秋千上居然坐着一只熊。

column2: You find a Ranger Army Knife! The tree sighs and smiles. It's much better now.
column3: 你找到了一把护林员多功能军刀！那棵树长舒一口气，满意地微笑着。它现在感觉好多了。

column2: You fix the broken duck. It quacks happily and flies off.
column3: 你修好了那只破损的鸭子。它高兴地嘎嘎叫着飞走了。

column3: 你修好了那只受伤的大象。它朝你道谢后撒腿跑开了。

column3: 你回到了洞穴中枢。

column3: 你穿过了彩虹之门。

column2: You place the stone Right Arm on the statue.
column3: 你将石制右臂安到雕像上。

column2: You place the toys in the correct boxes, and the closet door opens.
column3: 你把玩具归放进正确的箱子里，壁橱门随之开启。

column3: 你把汤倒进了杯子，手心感受到温热。

column3: 你拿起了金色的渔网。

column2: (ANNOUNCER)\\\\Patented Murray tech allows you to clean everything. From the biggest messes--
column3: (播报员)\\\\默里专利科技，轻松应对所有清洁难题。从最糟糕的混乱—
(播报员)\\\\相当酷！

column2: (ANNOUNCER)\\\\Roll on down to Chica's Party World!
column3: (播报员)\\\\快来奇卡的派对世界嗨起来！

column2: (ANNOUNCER)\\\\The solution is here, friend: Murray's Magic Coat-Rack!
column3: (播报员)\\\\朋友，终极解决方案来了：默里的魔法衣帽架！

column2: (ANNOUNCER)\\\\There are so many to choose from, but none of them fit every corner of your home.
column3: (播报员)\\\\市面上有很多选择，但没有一个能适合你家的每个角落。

column2: (ANNOUNCER)\\\\They repeat any song they hear or anything you say.
column3: (播报员)\\\\它们能模仿任何听到的歌曲和你说的话。

column2: (ANNOUNCER)\\\\Your family will love the new addition.
column3: (播报员)\\\\你的家人一定会喜欢这个新成员的。

column2: (ARNOLD))\\\\Wait. What? What are you? A computer? Your voice changed. What is going on?
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\等等，什么？你是谁？是一台电脑吗？你的声音变了，到底发生了什么？

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\Ah, man! That- that- That thing tried to kill me! I gotta get out of here.
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\天哪！那东西刚才差点杀了我！我得赶紧离开这里。
(阿诺德)\\\\看来这里没人。

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\I did everything you told me to.
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\我已经全照你说的做了。
(阿诺德)\\\\我恨你。
(阿诺德)\\\\我刚到了。
(阿诺德)\\\\不是！东西已经给你了！

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\Oh no no no! I almost died again!!\\\\You need to send help! Get me out of here, now!!
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\不不不！我又差点死了！！快派人来救我！马上带我离开这里！！

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\Okay... how am I supposed to get in?
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\那我应该怎么进去？
(阿诺德)\\\\那声音听起来很重要。刚才那是什么？

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\Wait, what? I can barely keep my eyes open!
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\等等，什么？我已经快睁不开眼睛了！

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\Well, since you asked, I just finished a 36-hour shift... been struggling to stay awake. Frankly, I tried to tell my manager that I can't work like this anymore...
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\既然你问了，我刚刚连续上了36小时的班……一直在硬撑保持清醒。说真的，我都跟经理说过我撑不下去了……

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\What? I just talked to you. You told me to give you the data diver and I could go home.
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\什么？我刚跟你说过话。你说让我把数据潜入器给你，我就能回家了。

column2: (ARNOLD)\\\\What? No! I'm doing it because you guys keep threatening to dock my pay and repo my truck!
column3: (阿诺德)\\\\什么？不是的！我这么做是因为你们一直威胁要扣我工资，还要把我的卡车收回去！
(阿诺德)\\\\哇啊！

(鲍森)\\\\嘟囔嘟囔……

column3: (鲍森)\\\\我已经竭尽全力了，霍斯。这就是我为你准备的，完美礼物！

column2: (BAWSON)\\\\Is that all is it? Perfect Present coming right up!
column3: (鲍森)\\\\就这些是吧？完美的礼物马上奉上！

column2: (BAWSON)\\\\Yes. Yes. You go enjoy that now.
column3: (鲍森)\\\\对，对。你慢慢享用吧。

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\Arrr we under attack? The ship be covered in… covered in… decorations?
column3: (船长)\\\\咦？我们被袭击了吗？船上怎么全是……全是……装饰品？
(船长)\\\\住手，水里的家伙！
(船长)\\\\走开！你这抱船狂！
(船长)\\\\可恶，霍斯！

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\Decorations… First Mate Foxy, arr ye havin’ a parrrrty?
column3: (船长)\\\\装饰品……一副手霍斯，你在办派对吗？

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\Did ye forget pirate rule number 22 - NO PARRRTIES!!
column3: (船长)\\\\你忘了海盗守则第22条—禁止开派对！！

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\Every sailor knows Rocktopi are drawn to boat parties!\\\\This is why sailors don’t have boat parties!
column3: (船长)\\\\每个水手都知道摇滚章鱼们最喜欢船上的派对！这就是水手绝不在船上办派对的原因！
(船长)\\\\霍斯，我的生日可是上周了！
(船长)\\\\霍斯，这场派对是给我办的？？
(船长)\\\\嘟囔嘟囔……
(船长)\\\\不许办派对！！

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\Party snacks?! Pirate rule number 1 - NO PARTY SNACKS!!
column3: (船长)\\\\派对零食？！海盗第一条铁律—绝不准有派对零食！！
(船长)\\\\吃我这一招！再来一下！
(船长)\\\\给我走跳板去。

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\Well done lads, ye all worked together for once. Like a real crew!\\\\You’ve made me the happiest Captain on the seven seas!
column3: (船长)\\\\干得漂亮，伙计们，难得大家一起合作了一回。简直像真正的船员了！\\\\你们让我成了七大洋上最开心的船长！
(船长)\\\\呀—这里闹腾什么呢？

column2: (CAPTAIN)\\\\…and pirate rule number 2 - NO DECORATIONS!! …aside from our flag that is…
column3: (船长)\\\\……还有，海盗第二条铁律—不许装饰！！……当然，除了我们的海盗旗……
(大卫)\\\\(低声哭泣起来)
(大卫)\\\\我爱你。
(大卫)\\\\好可怕。
(大卫)\\\\像什么？
(大卫)\\\\等等妈妈。妈妈最喜欢收礼物了。
(大卫)\\\\它在哪儿？
(大卫)\\\\它怎么长成那样？
(数码打字机器人)\\\\回到工作中。
(数码打字机器人)\\\\需要我闪电送达吗？
(数码打字机器人)\\\\我可以秒送到位。

column2: (DIGITYPER)\\\\I will make it snap snap snappy.
column3: (数码打字机器人)\\\\我保证让投递嗖嗖快。
(数码打字机器人)\\\\邮件送达。

column2: (DIGITYPER)\\\\Package, letter, parcel, post, postcard, card, communication, note, memo, memorandum, missive, report, news, dispatch, document, bulletin and epistle.
column3: (数码打字机器人)\\\\包裹、信件、快件、邮包、明信片、卡片、信息、便条、备忘、通知、书信、报告、新闻、调度、文档、公告，还有鸿雁传书。
