JACKIE:
Tag. You’re it.
column3:
(数码打字机器人)\\\\欢迎……新用户。

杰基:
捉到你啦。你就是被抓的那一个。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\(Until the next time something bad happens to you.)
column3: (调度员)\\\\(等到你下次又倒霉时再见。)

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\...And need I remind you to refer to section 9.041 of your contract?
column3: (调度员)\\\\……还需要我提醒你查查合同第9.041条吗？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\...How immoral would that be? Ha! But seriously, great job.
column3: (调度员)\\\\……这样做有多不道德？哈哈！不过说真的，干得不赖。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\...Not that anyone here at Fazbear Entertainment was wagering if you would survive or not...
column3: (调度员)\\\\……不是说费斯熊娱乐这里有谁在赌你能不能活着出来……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\...always being mindful of the fact that this... 'entity' could potentially be inside any costume or character that you see.
column3: (调度员)\\\\……时刻记住，这个……“存在”随时有可能藏在你看到的任何套装或者角色里。
(调度员)\\\\……不过啊，事后诸葛亮谁都会，对吧？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\...with the addition of the aforementioned homicidal tendencies, of course.
column3: (调度员)\\\\……当然，别忘了前面说的那点杀人倾向。
(调度员)\\\\干得漂亮。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\According to the building status log, most of the facility is out of power.
column3: (调度员)\\\\根据大楼的状态记录，大部分设施现在都停电了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Alright, take a deep breath and get back in there. Finish the job and that $25 gift certificate is as good as yours!
column3: (调度员)\\\\好了，深呼吸，然后再进去。把活干完，那25美元的礼品卡就归你了！
(调度员)\\\\太棒了，我们会着手调查的！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Amazing. Thanks for being a part of the Fazbear Team! Dispatch, out!
column3: (调度员)\\\\太好了。感谢你加入费斯熊团队！调度员下线！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\And after you find that schematic for us, we can certainly try to maybe find a way to probably save your life from it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\等你帮我们找到那份图纸后，我们或许真能想点办法，试试看把你从那玩意儿手里救出来。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\And better news. The motion sensors are now active.
column3: (调度员)\\\\还有好消息，动感传感器现在已经启动了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Another worker bee? A bumbling bee? Perhaps a busy bee.
column3: (调度员)\\\\又是一只工蜂？还是一只冒冒失失的小蜜蜂？也可能是个勤快蜂吧。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Anyway, head through the warehouse and you should reach the Admin Wing... eventually.
column3: (调度员)\\\\总之，穿过仓库，应该就能到行政区……迟早能到的。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Arnie, buddy, check in when you have a chance.
column3: (调度员)\\\\阿尔尼，哥们，有空就回个信儿。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Arnie, buddy, you’re making a huge mistake.
column3: (调度员)\\\\阿尔尼，老兄，你这是在犯大错啊。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Arnold! Hey buddy, this is dispatch with Fazbear Entertainment. How are you feeling?
column3: (调度员)\\\\阿诺德！嘿，伙计，这里是费斯熊娱乐的调度员。感觉怎么样？
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德，回去吧。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Arnold, I have to confess something...\\\\I am seriously impressed with your progress.\\\\At this rate, we'll be finished before dawn.
column3: (调度员)\\\\阿诺德，我得坦白点事儿……\\\\你现在的进展真让我佩服。\\\\照你这个速度，咱们天亮前都能收工。
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德，能听到吗？
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德，赶紧接话，完毕。
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德。嘿！
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德，醒醒，快起来！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Arnold. Why? Why would you come down here?
column3: (调度员)\\\\阿诺德，为什么？你为什么要跑到这里来？
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德？一切都还好吗？
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德？原来你在这儿！
(调度员)\\\\阿诺德？你在吗？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\As always, try to keep quiet and don't draw attention to yourself.\\\\Do that, and I'm positive nothing else bad is going to happen to you.
column3: (调度员)\\\\老规矩，尽量安静点，别引人注意。\\\\做到这点，我敢打包票，再也不会有倒霉事找上你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\As for your REAL job, your next target is the upgrade station in the demonstration theater.
column3: (调度员)\\\\说回你的“真正工作”，你下一个目标是演示剧场里的升级站。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\As per his contract, everything he's been working on for us is now legally ours, so we're sending you in to get it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\根据他的合同，他给我们干的所有东西现在全归我们合法所有，所以你得进去把它们拿出来。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\At some point the endoskeleton was exposed to some sort of violence, the details of which are a little fuzzy.
column3: (调度员)\\\\内骨骼曾在某个时候遭遇暴力破坏，具体细节还有些不清楚。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Awesome to hear. Well listen, we need you to take one more shift for us since you're our closest technician in the area.
column3: (调度员)\\\\很高兴听到这个。这样吧，你是这一带离我们最近的技术员，我们需要你再帮忙值一班。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Awesome, glad to see you made it here without any complications whatsoever!
column3: (调度员)\\\\太好了，看到你一路顺利到这儿真让人高兴！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Before you go, take a hand crank for the security fence.
column3: (调度员)\\\\在出发前，记得拿一只用于安全围栏的手摇曲柄。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\But first, the system says the data diver was updated to include "creator" permissions.
column3: (调度员)\\\\不过要先说明，系统显示数据驱动器已更新，增加了“创作者”权限。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\But for whatever reason, the warehouse is only accessible to admin permission staff. Makes no sense to me.
column3: (调度员)\\\\但不知什么原因，仓库还是只能管理员权限的人进入。我也搞不懂为什么。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\But you're just like the others. The other technicians. The workers.
column3: (调度员)\\\\不过你也跟其他人一样，和那些技术员、工人没什么两样。
(调度员)\\\\等会儿再联系。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Check out the computer map. You passed a power room on your way in.
column3: (调度员)\\\\看看电脑上的地图。你进来的路上经过了一个配电房。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Check the map. You can get there through the workshops.
column3: (调度员)\\\\查看一下地图。你可以从工坊过去。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Check the monitor. I am sending you a camera feed. Go there.
column3: (调度员)\\\\看一下监控，我正在给你发送摄像头画面，去那个位置。
(调度员)\\\\检查一下你的工具箱。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Check, check, check. Testing. Testing.  One, two, three…
column3: (调度员)\\\\检查、检查、检查。测试、测试。一、二、三……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Come back to the security office immediately. I found the location of another upgrade station.
column3: (调度员)\\\\立刻回安保办公室。我刚找到了另一个升级站的位置。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Come on back to the Security Office for further instructions.
column3: (调度员)\\\\快回安保办公室，听取进一步指示。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Did I mention we have access to the facility computer systems? Yeah. We can do it over the phone lines. Pretty cool.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我有说过我们现在能访问设施的计算机系统吗？对，我们可以通过电话线连进去。挺厉害的吧。
(调度员)\\\\别惹我。
(调度员)\\\\别惹我。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Don't call us, our lawyers will be calling you.
column3: (调度员)\\\\别联系我们，我们的律师会找你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Don't forget to come to the Security Office. Then you can go home.
column3: (调度员)\\\\别忘了来安保办公室，然后你就能回家了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Don’t you want a bonus? Or two bonuses? You can have a day off.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你不想要奖金吗？或者要两个？还可以休一天假。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Edwin kept them tucked away in his Executive Suite.
column3: (调度员)\\\\埃德温一直把它们藏在他的行政套房里。
(调度员)\\\\仅限员工进入。
(调度员)\\\\仅限员工进入。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Fazbear Entertainment has no other option but to let you go.
column3: (调度员)\\\\费斯熊娱乐别无选择，只能让你离职。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Fazbear Entertainment will hold you personally responsible for lost or stolen property.
column3: (调度员)\\\\费斯熊娱乐会追究你对遗失或失窃财产的个人责任。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Fazbear will send another. Maybe that one will help me.
column3: (调度员)\\\\费斯熊会再派一个人来，也许下一个能帮到我。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Finally, you have access to the Admin Wing. That's where Murray's office is located.\\\\And most importantly, the schematics.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你终于获得了行政区的通行权。默里的办公室就在那里面。\\\\更重要的是，那里还有设计图纸。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\From what we can tell, it was designed to keep Murray's son entertained while Murray worked.
column3: (调度员)\\\\据我们了解，这里原本是为了让默里工作的同时，他的儿子能有地方玩耍而特别设计的。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Get that schematic, and with some luck, you can deactivate that endoskeleton and collect it for us as well.
column3: (调度员)\\\\找到那份设计图，如果顺利的话，你还能帮我们关掉那台内骨骼并把它带回来。
(调度员)\\\\把数据潜入器交给我。
(调度员)\\\\干得不错。
(调度员)\\\\很棒，干得漂亮。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Good job. You can reach the Lobby from here.
column3: (调度员)\\\\干得好。你现在可以从这里进入大厅了。
(调度员)\\\\做得漂亮！
(调度员)\\\\一定在附近，继续找吧。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Great news. Power has been restored to this wing of the building. Overhead paging works.
column3: (调度员)\\\\好消息，这一侧的电力已经恢复，广播系统也可以用了。
(调度员)\\\\太棒了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Great. Head back to the Security Office, and I'll give you more instructions on what exactly we need you to retrieve for us.
column3: (调度员)\\\\很好。回到安全办公室，我会详细告诉你接下来需要找什么东西。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Great. They must have all gone home for the night.
column3: (调度员)\\\\很好，他们今晚估计都回家了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Ha! I love that enthusiasm! So anyway, this will be a piece of cake.
column3: (调度员)\\\\哈！我喜欢你的干劲！总之，这简直是小菜一碟。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\He was working on an endoskeleton that can adapt to any costume or character,\\\\large or small, with the ability to take on the persona of the character it occupies...
column3: (调度员)\\\\他在研发一种无论大小都能适配任意套装与角色的内骨骼，还能模拟所穿角色的性格和行为……
(调度员)\\\\回到安全办公室去吧。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Head back to where you first entered the building for further instructions.
column3: (调度员)\\\\回到你一开始进入大楼的地方，等待进一步指示。
(调度员)\\\\可以出发了，一切都结束了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Hey buddy. You know where you're going?\\\\Look for the Workshops. Check your map if you're lost.
column3: (调度员)\\\\嘿，伙计，你知道自己要去哪里吗？\\\\去找工坊，如果迷路记得看看地图。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Hey, Arnold, the system says you need a suit to get into the theater.
column3: (调度员)\\\\阿诺德，系统提示你需要一套套装才能进剧院。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Hey, you made it! I knew you would!
column3: (调度员)\\\\你做到了！我就知道你一定能行！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\How? I see you at the door.
column3: (调度员)\\\\怎么做到的？我明明看到你就在门口啊。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\How? I see you at the door.
column3: (调度员)\\\\怎么做到的？我明明看到你就在门口啊。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I am dying to know what happened in there.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我特别想知道你在里面遇到什么了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I can just smell that $25 gift certificate, can't you?
column3: (调度员)\\\\我都能闻到那张25美元礼品券的味道了，你是不是也闻到了？
(调度员)\\\\我没办法阻止它。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I don't know why you're still here.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我不明白你为什么还留在这里。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I don't think you could possibly understand how important this work is.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我觉得你根本无法体会这项工作有多重要。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I found the location of another upgrade station up in the show rooms.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我在展厅那儿找到了另一个升级站的位置。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I guess that means you're an artist now. Good job. I knew you could do it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\看来你现在已经是个艺术家了。干得漂亮，我早就知道你能行。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I hope you can do it without me. I'm trusting you with this. Got it?
column3: (调度员)\\\\这件事就交给你了，希望你没有我也能搞定。你明白了吗？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I know, the grind is exhilarating, isn't it? And we're so happy to have you on the Fazbear team!
column3: (调度员)\\\\我明白，这种折腾也挺让人上头的，对吧？我们很高兴你成为费斯熊团队的一员！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I need you in the security office.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我需要你去安全办公室一趟。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I protected you as well as I could.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我已经尽全力保护你了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I really don't know what the problem is...
column3: (调度员)\\\\我是真不知道问题出在哪……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I see a bonus in your future.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我预感你很快就会拿到奖金。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I see right through your simple shell game.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你这点小把戏我可一眼就能看穿。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I see right through your simple shell game.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你这点小把戏我可一眼就能看穿。
(调度员)\\\\我看到你就在里面……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I see your mouth moving, but I ‘m not hearing anything. There must be a problem with your mic.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我看到你嘴巴在动，但我一点声音也没听见。你的麦克风好像出问题了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I thought you were different. I thought you might understand.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我以为你不一样，以为你能懂我。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I'll direct you where you need to go next. I would urge caution, however,\\\\we're getting some very confusing readings up ahead.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我接下来会指引你该往哪走。不过我要提醒你小心点，前面的监测数据很混乱。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I'm going to have to keep it locked until you hand over that device.
column3: (调度员)\\\\除非你把那个装置交出来，不然这门我就一直锁着。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I'm guessing you took care of it. Well done.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我猜你已经搞定了。干得不错。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I'm sure you're right! Those motion sensors never tell the truth!
column3: (调度员)\\\\我肯定你说得没错！那些运动传感器从来不靠谱！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I've got to warn you, it's not close to your current location at all.\\\\So we won't be in communication for a while.
column3: (调度员)\\\\得提醒你，那里离你现在的位置很远，咱们一阵子可能联系不上。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\I've opened the garage for you. You can just hop in your van and drive home.
column3: (调度员)\\\\车库已经给你开了门，你现在可以直接开着你的面包车回家了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\If that's not incentive enough to find the schematic, then I don't know what is!
column3: (调度员)\\\\要是这都还不能激发你去找那份原理图，我真就没招了！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\If you are talking, I still can't hear you.
column3: (调度员)\\\\如果你在说话，我还是一点没听见。
(调度员)\\\\如果你在的话，接一下。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\If you can hear me, pick up.
column3: (调度员)\\\\如果你能听见我，接个话。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\In many ways, tonight has been a comedy of errors. A Jester would suit you well.
column3: (调度员)\\\\今晚真是一场混乱的大闹剧，穿身小丑套装还挺适合你的。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It cannot see you in that suit, but I can.
column3: (调度员)\\\\那套套装里面它看不到你，但我可能看得清清楚楚。
(调度员)\\\\它跟着你来了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It looks like you don’t have a security level high enough to leave this office, or enter the power room for that matter.
column3: (调度员)\\\\看来你的安全权限还不够高，既不能离开这个办公室，也进不了配电室。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It should be in the van. Ritchie slipped it in your tool box during the last job. Just in case…
column3: (调度员)\\\\那东西应该还在货车上。上次行动时，里奇顺手塞进了你的工具箱。以防万一……
(调度员)\\\\它会抓到你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It would mimic the actions of those around it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\它会模仿身边人的举动。
(调度员)\\\\锁上了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It's on the upper floor of the Administration Wing.
column3: (调度员)\\\\它在行政区的楼上。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It's something we haven't seen before. I'm sure it's nothing, but just be careful in case it's something.
column3: (调度员)\\\\这是我们从未见过的玩意儿。或许没什么大不了，但你还是小心点，以防万一。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\It’s very important that you update the Data Diver whenever you find an Access Station. This is not optional.
column3: (调度员)\\\\每次找到接入终端时，都必须立刻更新数据潜入器，这不是可有可无的选项。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Just follow the soothing sound of my voice.
column3: (调度员)\\\\只管跟着我平稳的声音走。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Just pick it up when you find it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\找到了就直接拿起来。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Just put it in the inventory machine. It's right there in the corner...
column3: (调度员)\\\\只要把它投进盘点机。就在角落里……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Kinda looks like a walkie talkie with two prongs sticking out the top.
column3: (调度员)\\\\它看起来像个对讲机，上面还竖着两个插针。
(调度员)\\\\环顾一下四周。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Look for a control station. You should be able to get those doors to open by restarting the Welcome Show program.
column3: (调度员)\\\\找个控制台试试。你可以通过重启迎宾秀程序来打开那扇门。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Look. I share your frustration. I take it the Warehouse Manager’s office was a bust.  That’s too bad.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我理解你的挫败感，我猜你在仓库经理办公室那边一无所获，可惜了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Looks like you can get one from the “Inventory Tube System”.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你可以从“库存管道系统”那儿拿到一个。
(调度员)\\\\快点。
(调度员)\\\\必须节省电力。
(调度员)\\\\必须节省电力。
(调度员)\\\\必须节省电力。
(调度员)\\\\禁止进入。
(调度员)\\\\禁止进入。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\No one doubted you for a second, and those who did are now out $20...
column3: (调度员)\\\\没人怀疑过你一秒钟，倒是那些怀疑你的人现在都输了二十美元……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\No. You did everything I asked up to this point. You were an obedient dog. A good dog.
column3: (调度员)\\\\不，你做到了我要求的一切，到目前为止像只乖巧的狗，真不错。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Not a problem, we just need to find stations to upgrade your Data Diver until you can gain access.
column3: (调度员)\\\\没事儿，我们只需去升级你的数据潜入器，直到你拿到进入权限。
(调度员)\\\\开局不太妙啊……
(调度员)\\\\现在去找配电室。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Now that you're there (and it would be very difficult for you to turn back),\\\\I should probably level with you a little.
column3: (调度员)\\\\既然你已经在那里了(回头也几乎不可能)，那我得跟你坦白点事。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Now, get in there and I'll follow up with more information when you reach the security office.
column3: (调度员)\\\\好了，进去吧。等你到了安全办公室，我会再给你详细指示。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Now, get in there and retrieve our property.
column3: (调度员)\\\\好了，进去，把我们的东西带出来。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Now, it's your turn to play dress up.
column3: (调度员)\\\\现在轮到你装扮了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Now, what're you waiting for? Keep on truckin’.
column3: (调度员)\\\\还等什么？继续干活。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Now, you are going to love this. I have located the Fazbear project blueprints.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你肯定会喜欢这个。我找到了费斯熊项目的蓝图。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Obviously this endoskeleton that seems to want to kill you has encountered some unfortunate glitches,\\\\but that doesn't mean the idea isn't sound or valuable.
column3: (调度员)\\\\显然，这个想杀你的内骨骼因为一些糟糕的故障变得危险，但这不代表这个设计没有价值。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Oh good, you found the Upgrade Station for the Data Diver. You’ll need it to reach the different areas in the complex.
column3: (调度员)\\\\太好了，你找到了数据潜入器的升级站。你需要它才能进入设施里的其他区域。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Oh my. It looks like we do have one big issue.
column3: (调度员)\\\\唔，看来我们有个大麻烦了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Oh, and try to be careful along the way - we are seeing some strange readings in the area.
column3: (调度员)\\\\另外，路上小心—我们这片区域监测到了一些异常读数。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Oh… Huh. Well, that is strange… Uhhh…\\\\Nothing to worry about. Just come back to the Security Office for further instruction.
column3: (调度员)\\\\呃……这还真奇怪……不过没什么好担心的，回安全办公室听下步指示吧。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Ol' Murray made some neat stuff over the years, and unfortunately it seems that one of his most creative inventions may have encountered some...\\\\homicidal glitches in its programming.
column3: (调度员)\\\\老默里这些年来造了不少奇妙的玩意儿，但很遗憾，他最有创意的一个发明，可能程序里出现了……杀人故障。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Once you put the Data Diver in the inventory system, you can clock out and get some rest. Go home.
column3: (调度员)\\\\等你把数据潜入器接入库存系统后，就可以打卡下班回家了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Or a bunny. Running from danger. Scared and stupid. Searching for a hole to hide in.
column3: (调度员)\\\\或者说你就像只兔子，拼命逃命，害怕又蠢，只想找个洞藏起来。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Or a bunny. Running from danger. Scared and stupid. Searching for a hole to hide in.
column3: (调度员)\\\\或者说你就像只兔子，拼命逃命，害怕又蠢，只想找个洞藏起来。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Our motion sensors indicate that someone is still inside the building moving around\\\\although the signal is a bit erratic, but we don't expect any kind of confrontation.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们的探测器显示，楼里还有人在活动，虽然信号有点不稳定，但应该不会有冲突发生。
(调度员)\\\\完毕。
(调度员)\\\\完毕。
(调度员)\\\\完毕。
(调度员)\\\\请前往安全办公室。
(调度员)\\\\请回应，完毕。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Put that Data Diver in the inventory system. It will go right to where it is needed.
column3: (调度员)\\\\把数据潜入器接入库存系统，它会被自动送到需要的地方。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Read the sign. That is a no-exit door.
column3: (调度员)\\\\请看清标志，那是无出口门。
(调度员)\\\\请回应，完毕。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Restoring power should be your first priority… Unless you enjoy fumbling around in the dark all night.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你现在的头等大事就是恢复电力……除非你喜欢整夜在黑里瞎摸。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Right now you should focus on finding a way to turn the power back on!
column3: (调度员)\\\\你现在应该专心想办法，把电再开起来！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Sleeping on the job? I'm disappointed. This is going in your personal file.
column3: (调度员)\\\\上班打瞌睡？真让我失望。这会记进你的个人档案里。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\So you admit it? You misplaced our company property.
column3: (调度员)\\\\所以你承认了？把公司财产弄丢了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\So, it seems that maybe distraction and avoidance are your best tools,\\\\as a direct confrontation will likely result in the loss of some limbs.
column3: (调度员)\\\\看来转移注意力和回避冲突才是你的看家本领，毕竟直接对抗很可能让你丢掉几条胳膊腿。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\So, let's talk about what you're there to find.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们还是来说说你此行需要找的东西吧。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\So, we did some digging to learn more about that bothersome endoskeleton that keeps relentlessly pursuing you.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们调查了一下，想多了解那个死缠烂打追你的讨厌内骨骼。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Some mysteries are never meant to be solved.
column3: (调度员)\\\\有些谜团天生就是解不开的。
(调度员)\\\\立刻停下你手头的事情。
(调度员)\\\\立刻停下你手头的事情。
(调度员)\\\\住手……那个我还需要……
(调度员)\\\\住手……那个我还需要……
(调度员)\\\\住手……那个我还需要……
(调度员)\\\\那个区域禁止入内。
(调度员)\\\\动作还挺快的嘛。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\That “Data Diver” is your master key to the MCM facility. Do not lose it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\那台“数据潜入器”是你进出MCM设施的万能钥匙，千万别弄丢了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\That's the big machine in the Security Office. Should be active…now.
column3: (调度员)\\\\那就是安保办公室的大机器。现在应该启动了……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\The Data Diver has Exec permissions and you found the blueprints.
column3: (调度员)\\\\数据潜入器有高权限，你还拿到了蓝图。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\The Lobby doors have been locked by some “showtime” run errors whatever that means.
column3: (调度员)\\\\大厅的门被什么“表演时间”运行错误给锁了—这啥意思我也说不清。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\The best way to the Admin wing is through the warehouse.\\\\That’s the big room you’ve been standing in front of all night.
column3: (调度员)\\\\去行政区最佳路线得穿过仓库。也就是你整个晚上都站在门口的那个大房间。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\The previous technicians considered it an honor to lose limbs in the service of their company,\\\\and I'm sure they would tell you that themselves if they hadn't died from blood loss.
column3: (调度员)\\\\前任技术员们觉得为公司断胳膊断腿是光荣，要不是失血过多死了现在肯定会亲口告诉你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\The system was flooded with alarms and alerts, and then it all stopped.
column3: (调度员)\\\\一阵报警和提示音把系统搞得乱七八糟，紧接着全都消停了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\The upgrade machine should be active… now.
column3: (调度员)\\\\升级机现在应该也能用了……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Then you bit the hand that fed you.
column3: (调度员)\\\\之后你居然反咬一口。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Then you can just walk right out and head home.
column3: (调度员)\\\\那你就能直接离开，安心回家了。
(调度员)\\\\你这不是在这儿呢嘛。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\These things happen, and I'm sure it's nothing to worry about,\\\\but you should probably worry about it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\这事儿常有，估计没啥大问题，不过你恐怕还是得上点心。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\They are all over the facility. In fact, there is a station in the warehouse manager's office. You should head there next.
column3: (调度员)\\\\它们遍布整个设施。实际上，仓库经理办公室里就有一台终端。你接下来应该去那里。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\They didn't listen and it caught them all.
column3: (调度员)\\\\他们不听劝，结果全都没逃过那一劫。
(调度员)\\\\仔细想想你现在的举动……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\This 'Mimic' endoskeleton then copied that violent behavior.
column3: (调度员)\\\\这个名为“模拟”的内骨骼后来照搬了那种暴力行为。
(调度员)\\\\这里是禁区，禁止进入。
(调度员)\\\\这里是禁区，禁止进入。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\This is exactly what we've been looking for all night.
column3: (调度员)\\\\这正是我们整晚在寻找的东西。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\To access the building, you have been provided with a “Data Diver” tool.
column3: (调度员)\\\\为了进入大楼，你收到了一件“数据潜入器”工具。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Unfortunately, we came up with those ideas before the last technicians were sent in,\\\\and they ended up with less than positive results.
column3: (调度员)\\\\很遗憾，我们在上一批技术员进去前就想到了这些对策，结果反而很惨。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Use that Data Diver upgrade machine. It should give you clearance to open the door.
column3: (调度员)\\\\去用那个数据潜入器升级机吧，它会让你获得开门权限。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We came up with some great ideas on how to protect yourself.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们想出了一些保护你自身的好办法。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We expect you'll succeed where they failed. One out of three Fazbear Employees has confidence in you, so go get 'em tiger!
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们希望你能做得比他们更好。至今有三分之一的费斯熊员工相信你，所以放手去干吧，虎仔！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We had this contractor named Edwin Murray; he was developing some tech for us but he's gone quiet.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们有个叫埃德温·默里的合同工；他曾为我们开发设备，但他现在彻底失联了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We think that endoskeleton has a lot of potential, and that's why we want you to retrieve Murray's original schematic for it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们认为那台内骨骼设备还有很大发展空间，这也是我们要你找回默里的原始设计图的原因。
(调度员)\\\\我们很快会再联系你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We'll be working on some ideas on how to neutralize this rogue endoskeleton,\\\\but in the meantime, just try to be quiet, careful, and focused on the task at hand...
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们正在想办法解决这个失控的内骨骼，不过在此期间，你要保持安静、小心，并时刻专注任务……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We'll follow up with more instructions soon. For now, just follow these directions and find your way into that building!
column3: (调度员)\\\\很快会有更多指示。现在先按照这些步骤，设法进入那栋楼！

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We're still detecting movement in the building that you're in,\\\\and we have a little bit of an idea as to what it might be.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们仍在监测你所在大楼内有异常活动，而且多少知道是什么原因了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\We've been trying to get a hold of you all night.
column3: (调度员)\\\\我们一整晚都在试图联系你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Well done, Arnie! I didn't think you could do it, but here you are.
column3: (调度员)\\\\干得漂亮，阿尼！我本来没想到你能做成，但你果然办到了。
(调度员)\\\\你在干嘛，阿诺德？
(调度员)\\\\你到底在做什么？
(调度员)\\\\你以为会发生什么？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\What took you so long? Don't get lazy on the job now, we need you to stay focused!
column3: (调度员)\\\\怎么花了这么久？现在可别偷懒了，我们还需要你打起精神来！
(调度员)\\\\怎么这么久还没好……？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\When he catches you, which one will he choose?
column3: (调度员)\\\\他要是抓住你，你觉得他会选哪一个？
(调度员)\\\\你去哪儿了？
(调度员)\\\\你去哪儿了？
(调度员)\\\\你以为自己要去哪儿？
(调度员)\\\\你是哪一个？
(调度员)\\\\你到底是哪一个？
(调度员)\\\\你内心深处到底是谁？
(调度员)\\\\哎，慢点，冷静点兄弟。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Why are you trying to come in here?
column3: (调度员)\\\\你为什么非要进来这里？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Why are you trying to come in here?
column3: (调度员)\\\\你为什么非要进来这里？
(调度员)\\\\你为什么不回话？
(调度员)\\\\你为什么不相信我？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Without power, you will trap us both down here in the dark.
column3: (调度员)\\\\没电的话，你会把我们俩都困在这下面的黑暗里。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Without power, you will trap us both down here in the dark.
column3: (调度员)\\\\没电的话，你会把我们俩都困在这下面的黑暗里。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You are clever, but you need to stop messing with things you don’t understand.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你确实很聪明，但别再碰那些你不懂的东西了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You can get there if you head back through the welcome show. That’s the room back where you entered the building.
column3: (调度员)\\\\从迎宾展厅回去就行了，那就是你最开始进楼时走过的房间。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You can see it through that window. Guess you should have gone there first.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你能透过那扇窗户看到。看来你本该第一时间去那里的。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You can't fool me thought; you're just trying to snag one of those $25 gift certificates at the end of the year for outstanding performance!
column3: (调度员)\\\\你骗不了我，你就是想年底拼那张25美元的杰出员工礼品券吧！
(调度员)\\\\你骗不了我。
(调度员)\\\\你骗不了我。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You could have helped. If you had just given me the schematics, we could have fixed things.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你其实能帮上忙的。如果你早把图纸交给我，一切都能修好。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You did everything else that was asked of you. Why the change of heart?
column3: (调度员)\\\\你其他的事都按要求做了，为什么现在突然变卦？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You found the schematics? Great. Get back to the security office right away. Time to wrap things up.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你找到图纸了吗？太好了，赶紧回安全办公室，该收尾了。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You got the blueprints? Great. Get back to the security office right away.\\\\Time to wrap things up.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你拿到蓝图了？太棒了，快点回安全办公室—该收尾了。
(调度员)\\\\你已经做出了选择。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You haven't seen anything unusual yet, have you?
column3: (调度员)\\\\你还没有碰上什么异常的东西吧？

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You know where you're going? Look for the workshops. Check your map if you are lost.
column3: (调度员)\\\\知道自己要去哪儿吗？去找工坊，迷路的话看下地图。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You made it the farthest! Farther than I had expected. I can't believe it was you.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你是走得最远的那个！比我预期的都远。我简直不敢相信是你。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You need to reach Murray's Executive Suite, that's where the schematic most likely is.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你得去默里的行政套房，图纸很可能就在那儿。
(调度员)\\\\你这么做，把我们俩都陷进危险里了……
(调度员)\\\\你这么做，让我们俩都处于风险之中……

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You should have done what you were told.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你本该按照吩咐去做的。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You should have given me what I wanted and gone home.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你本该把我想要的给我，然后回自己家去。
(调度员)\\\\你最好查查那件事。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You wouldn’t leave without finishing your job, would you? Of course not.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你不会半途而废地离开，对吧？当然不会。
(调度员)\\\\你快要完成了。
(调度员)\\\\你全部搞定了。好好去享受你的人生吧。
(调度员)\\\\你骗不了任何人。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You've been doing so well all night.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你这整晚表现得都很出色。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You've done everything you came here to do.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你已经完成了自己该做的所有事。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You've used it before. Don't pretend you don't know how it works.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你之前用过它，别装作不懂它怎么用。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\Your Data Diver doesn't have executive permission yet, so you can't get anywhere near it.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你的数据潜入器还没有高权限，所以你根本接近不了那边。

column2: (DISPATCH)\\\\You’re not going to make it out of here alive.
column3: (调度员)\\\\你可别指望能活着离开这里。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\"But Edwin, how does it work?" you may ask. Well, we collect various discarded materials.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\"但埃德温，这东西到底是怎么工作的呢？”你可能会问。呃，就是我们会把各种丢弃的材料收集起来。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\(Laughs) Oh. Get back to work, you.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\(笑)哎呀。你赶紧去干活吧。
(埃德温)\\\\(笑)每次都能让我忍不住笑出来。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\(laughs) Oh. Get back to work, you.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\(笑)哎呀。去干活吧你。
(埃德温)\\\\(剧烈咳嗽)

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\...And I guess what I'm trying to say is, I can't think of a future without you.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\……我想说的是，我真的没法想象没有你的未来。
(埃德温)\\\\……而且你做的木偶真是最棒的。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\...And you're also really pretty. Like 'asymmetrical' pretty. Uh, I should have led with that.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\……还有，你真的很漂亮，属于那种“非对称”的美。呃，其实我本该第一句就说这个。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\...And you're fun and funny. Not a lot of things really make me happy, but... but you do.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\……还有，你很有趣，也很幽默。很少有事能让我开心，但是……你可以。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A bunny hopped over and offered to play cards.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\有只兔子跳过来，想要一起打牌。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A bunny hopped over and offered to play cards. But they\\\\couldn’t agree on the game. The bunny was sad.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\有只兔子跳过来想打牌，但他们\\一直没商量好玩什么游戏。兔子感到有点难过。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A clumsy chicken came and spilled her marbles. They had fun picking them up.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只笨手笨脚的母鸡过来，把她的玻璃珠撒了一地。他们边捡边玩，玩得很开心。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A clumsy chicken joined them and they went out for ice cream but she dropped all their ice cream! Oh no!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只笨手笨脚的母鸡加入了大家，他们一起去吃冰淇淋，可她把所有的冰淇淋都掉在地上了！天哪！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A pesky little puppy yapped and played fetch.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只顽皮的小狗汪汪叫着，要大家和它玩你扔我捡的游戏。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A pesky puppy played fetch by itself on the beach.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只淘气的小狗独自在沙滩上玩扔拾游戏。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A pesky puppy yipped and yapped. She made so much noise that she gave everyone a headache.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只小狗不停地又叫又闹，吵得大家头都疼了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A roly poly bear joined the others and offered his honey. But then he spilled it all over them. Oh no!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只胖胖圆圆的熊也加入进来，还递上了自己的蜂蜜，结果一不小心全洒到了大家身上。糟糕！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A roly poly bear sat down and offered a pot of honey. They ate with glee.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只胖乎乎的熊坐下，拿出一罐蜂蜜，他们高高兴兴地一起享用。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A rumbly tumbly bear sang sweetly by a big blue lake.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只咕咕作响的大肚子熊，在湛蓝的大湖边唱起了甜美的歌谣。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\A wily fox buckled swashes in his pirate ship.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只狡猾的狐狸，在他的海盗船上大显身手。
(埃德温)\\\\更多故事模板，敬请选购。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\All this time wasted! I should have been having fun with him, playing games and teaching him how to make things… But, I didn’t.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这些时间都白白浪费了！我本应该和他一起开心地玩耍、做游戏、教他制作各种东西……可我没有做到。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Amazing, if I do say so myself.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\说实话，真是太棒了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\An angry alligator came by and promised not to eat anyone. But then he ate one of them.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只愤怒的鳄鱼出现了，还承诺不会吃掉任何一个人。结果最后，他还是吃了他们中的一个。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\An angry alligator came by and promised not to eat anyone. They had carrots instead.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只愤怒的鳄鱼来了，他答应不吃任何人，大家于是改吃胡萝卜了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\An angry alligator was swimming in the lake.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\一只生气的鳄鱼正在湖里游泳。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\And no, you can’t clear out your desks! You stole my work.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\别想清空你们的办公桌！你们可是偷了我的作品！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\And of course, you'll save a fortune on production costs!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你当然也能大大节省制作成本！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\And that was my patented “Demo-tronic Welcome Show”.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这就是我独有的“样品特技迎宾秀”。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\And what we can't use is broken down into its basic components which we then sell at a profit.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那些无法使用的东西都会被拆解成基础零件，然后我们再把它们卖出去赚利润。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Anything you want. It can fit into any costume we’ve created.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你想要什么都可以。它能适配我们已经做好的任何套装。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Anyway, you are the most amazing artist and creator I have ever been lucky enough to employ.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\无论如何，你是我所雇过最棒的艺术家和创作者。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Are the costs of writers, crew, and puppeteers holding you back?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\作家、剧组和木偶演员的成本让你犹豫不前吗？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Are they insane? The look of these new animatronics is Fiona's design and they're great.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\他们疯了吗？这些新机器人偶的外观可是菲奥娜设计的，非常出色。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Are you thinking of getting into the children's television entertainment space?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你是不是也想进入儿童电视娱乐行业啊？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Arr arr arr! Ahoy there! Shiver me timbers!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\啊哈哈哈！喂，朋友，天哪！(海盗腔)
(埃德温)\\\\啊哈！呀—啊啊啊！(海盗腔)
(埃德温)\\\\啊哈！！呀—啊啊啊啊！(海盗腔)
(埃德温)\\\\啊哈哈哈！！呀—啊啊啊啊啊！(海盗腔)

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Attention all personnel. The power surges have become more… frequent. Please use extreme caution when venturing down into the tunnels.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\全体人员注意。近期电力波动越来越频繁。请下到隧道时务必格外小心。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Attention traitors, admin wing permissions have been revoked.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\注意，叛徒们，行政区权限已被取消。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Basically, we take trash and turn it into cash.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\简单来说，我们就是把垃圾变成了钱。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Because money is green - not the old parts.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\因为要变绿的，是钞票，不是那些旧零件。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Besides, David loves the new slide. It'll be fine.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\再说了，大卫很喜欢新的滑梯。没问题的。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Besides, he’s got plenty more birthdays. Next year will be even better!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\而且，他还有许多生日呢。明年一定更棒！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Better start opening. There’s a lot to open… I gotta get back to work.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\快点开始拆吧，这里还有好多要开……我得赶回去工作了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\But I had the best idea. Could you make a quick instructional tape telling staff how to fix it?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\不过我突然有个超棒的主意。你能不能录个简短的教学视频，教员工怎么修理它？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Come in and see what Murray’s can do for your carnival, amusement park, midway or funfair.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\欢迎进来看一看，看看默里能为你的嘉年华、游乐园、游艺场或者游乐会带来些什么惊喜！
(埃德温)\\\\大卫，妈妈已经走了……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\David. I want to introduce you to someone. This is M1.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\大卫，来，我给你介绍一个人。这是M1。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\David’s two years old. He won’t remember a thing.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\大卫才两岁，他什么都不会记得的。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Do you remember how our story begins?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你还记得我们的故事是怎么开始的吗？
(埃德温)\\\\多莉，跟大家说说你是做什么的吧。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Don’t forget that everything you have seen and will see is available for purchase or lease.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\别忘了，无论你见到还是即将看到的一切，都可以买到或租用！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Don’t forget, every one of my creations are available for purchase or lease.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\别忘了，我的每一件作品都可以出售或者出租！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Edwin, Edwin Murray. This is my dad’s place. But that doesn’t matter…
column3: (埃德温)\\\\埃德温，埃德温·默里。这是我父亲的产业，但那都不重要……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Edwin, never forget. They’re behind it. Don’t trust them. Never tell them. They want to destroy you. Dad was right.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\埃德温，永远不要忘记。他们在背后捣鬼。别相信他们，千万别告诉他们。他们想毁了你。爸爸说得没错。
(埃德温)\\\\紧急情况……请求支援。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Every copy has failed. I don't even know why it worked the first time, but it did. It's just not ready.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\每一个副本都失败了。我甚至不知道第一次为什么能成功，但当时就是成功了。现在还不行，还没准备好。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Every time it breaks, I get pulled away to reset the thing. These disruptions totally throw off my vibe.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\每次设备坏掉，我就得被叫去重新设置。这些突发状况完全打乱了我的状态。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Excuse me. Can I borrow your voice for a project?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\不好意思，可以借用你的声音帮我做个项目吗？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Fiona was right. They don't think of me as a friend anymore.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\菲奥娜说得对，他们已经不再把我当朋友了。
(埃德温)\\\\菲奥娜，这是你做的吗？
(埃德温)\\\\菲奥娜，给你个惊喜！是我，埃德温。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\First they approve the art. Then they approve the proofs. Now, they change their minds when we're so close to final.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\他们先是通过艺术稿，然后批复样品。可现在我们都快定稿了，他们却又反悔了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\For all deliveries and work inquiries, the “Client and Deliveries Entrance” is located around the side of the building.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\所有送货和业务咨询，请从大楼侧面的“客户与送货入口”进来。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\For the last time, NO. It wouldn’t be him.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我最后说一次：不，不可能是他。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Great job. You just continue to surprise me. I think we’re ready.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\干得漂亮。你总是让我刮目相看。我觉得我们已经准备好了。
(埃德温)\\\\生日快乐，小伙子！
(埃德温)\\\\生日快乐，小伙子。
(埃德温)\\\\生日快乐，小伙子。
(埃德温)\\\\你好。喂？有人吗？完毕。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Here, there's no need for a cast or crew.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\在这里，不需要演员或剧组。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\He’s gone. He’s gone and now everyone is asking me what to do? And I don’t know anything.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\他走了。他走了，现在大家都问我怎么办？可我什么都不知道。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Honey, that stupid elevator keeps acting up.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\亲爱的，那部破电梯又犯毛病了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I am talking about broken midway games, costumes, computer and\\\\television parts, vacuum cleaners, toasters, and precious metals.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我说的是坏掉的游乐设施，演出服，电脑和电视零件，吸尘器，烤面包机，还有贵金属。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I can watch him play while I'm loading and unloading freight, and he'll be under watch at all times out there.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我能在搬运货物的时候看着他，而且他在外面会一直在视线范围内。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I can’t do this alone… The change orders are killing me. Our employees, my friends, they keep leaving.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我一个人做不了……这些变更指令快把我逼疯了。我们的员工，我的朋友们，都不断地离开。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I can’t move. I can’t feel my legs…
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我动不了了，腿一点感觉也没有……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I can’t run a company. I’m not ready… I can’t fill his shoes. He knew it. Everyone knew it.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我根本没法经营公司，我还没准备好……我真的无法接替他的位置。他知道，大家都明白。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I don’t know. This is all so much…
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我也不知道，这一切实在太压抑了……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I feel stupid recording this, but I just hope, somehow, that you can still hear me.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我觉得录这个挺傻的，但我只是希望，不管怎样，你还能听到我。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I guess I would have to say, “helpful.” At its core, it is helpful.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我想我应该说，是“有帮助”。本质上，它确实很有用。
(埃德温)\\\\大概是吧。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I have some very important TV people coming to look at the show template. I can't have the projector breaking again!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\有几位很重要的电视台人士要来看演出模板，我可不能再让投影仪出问题了！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I heard you were a puppeteer and I wanted to record your voice.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我听说你是木偶师，所以我想把你的声音录下来。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I know you're my lawyer and all, but there's no regulation that says I can't have it there, so just get off my back.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我知道你是我的律师，但没有哪条规定说我不能把它放在那里，所以别再唠叨了。
(埃德温)\\\\我爱你。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I made it. It’s part of this new system I’m working on.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那是我做的，是我正在设计的新系统的一部分。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I miss my friends. Our friends. I miss you.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我很想念我的朋友，我们的朋友。我也很想你。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I miss you more than you’ll ever know.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我对你的思念，远远超过你能想象。
(埃德温)\\\\我真的很想你。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I thought it'd be fun to go with a doll hospital theme. Pretty neat, huh?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我觉得把主题定成娃娃医院会很有趣。是不是很棒？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I want to keep making magic and sharing our creations with the world forever.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我想要一直创造“魔法”，永远把我们的作品带给全世界。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I'm very excited about our next show room.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我对我们的下一个展演厅非常期待。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\If writers have you blocked, use an MCM story template.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\如果写作被卡住了，就用MCM故事模板吧。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Isn’t that nice! So what happens next?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\是不是很棒！那接下来会发生什么呢？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\It doesn't matter... I'm not changing a single bit of her work and they can't make me.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\没关系……我一丁点都不会改动她的作品，他们也逼不了我。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\It would be so much easier to keep using the Springlocks.  Just hire some teens to wear the suits like we always do.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\继续用弹簧锁会轻松很多。只要像以前那样雇些年轻人穿这些套装就好了。
(埃德温)\\\\情节都能自然而然地发展出来。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\It’s a new type of audio cassette recorder.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这是一种新型的卡带录音机。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\It’s an endo skeleton. It won’t always look like this. It’ll wear fun costumes.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这是一个内部骨架，将来不会一直长这样，到时候会穿上有趣的套装。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\I’m… I’m sorry, M2. I… lost my temper. I was always going to fix you…
column3: (埃德温)\\\\……对不起，M2。我……我刚刚发脾气了。我一直是想修好你的……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Just give me a minute. I had the best idea.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\给我一点时间，我刚刚想到一个超棒的主意！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Just speak into the microphone and it’ll be sent to me like a work memo.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\只要对着麦克风说话，它就会像工作备忘录那样发到我这里来。
(埃德温)\\\\继续找……它应该就在这附近……
(埃德温)\\\\你指的是，应该看起来像什么？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Look, I get your concerns, I do, but they're all just groundless. This is the perfect spot for David's playground.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\听着，我明白你的担忧，真的，但这些担心都没有根据。这儿就是大卫游乐场的最佳位置。
(埃德温)\\\\爱你哦！
(埃德温)\\\\M2，帮帮我……
(埃德温)\\\\M2，回应一下。
(埃德温)\\\\M2，快点回应！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Maybe I’ll go find someone to sell your stuff to. How does that feel?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\也许我该去找个人把你的东西全卖掉，你觉得怎么样？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Maybe… rebrand? We could start making some of my inventions for real.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\也许……换个新名字？我们可以真的把我的一些发明投入生产了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\No difficult puppeteers, demanding actors or moody directors needed.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\不需要那些难伺候的木偶师、挑剔的演员或者爱发脾气的导演。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\No no. He loves it. Look. See, he loves it.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\不是的不是的。他真的很喜欢。看嘛，他很喜欢的。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\None of this makes sense. I'm almost done. Why change it now?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这一切都不合理。我马上就要完成了，为什么现在要改呢？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Not all gone, buddy… In a way she’s here. She’s with us. Mommy will always be here watching over us.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\不是全部都没了，伙计……实际上她还在这里，她陪着我们。妈妈会一直守护在我们身边。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Notice to all workers. All late night shenanigans are to stop immediately.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\通知所有员工，所有深夜恶作剧即刻终止。
(埃德温)\\\\现在该睡觉啦。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Now your jackets, purses and coffee mugs and anything else belongs to me.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\现在起，你们的外套、包包、咖啡杯，还有其他的东西都归我了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Now, sit back and enjoy the demonstration.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\现在，请大家靠好，欣赏演示吧。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Oh no! That’s not how the story went!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\糟了！故事不是这么讲的！
(埃德温)\\\\天呐！他们干了什么？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Oh. I don’t know. I haven’t thought of a name yet.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\呃……我还没想好名字呢。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Oh... Dummy, start over. Aw, come on... Rewind not working...\\\\Well, uh, keep going. Just, uh Fiona, ignore that part.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\呃……重来，傻瓜。哎，拜托……倒带又坏了……好吧，呃，那继续吧。菲奥娜，你就当那一段没发生。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Ok great. I need you to take over now and make dinner? I gotta get back to it.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\太好了。现在你能接手去做晚餐吗？我得继续忙去了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Ok. Everyone hide. Fiona, go get him. I left him out at the playground.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\好，大家藏起来。菲奥娜，快去把他接回来，我把他丢在游乐场了。
(埃德温)\\\\从前有一个……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\One of our sales reps will be along shortly.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我们的一位销售代表马上就会过来服务您。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Our patented "Stage Manager" software keeps your show on track and condensed to fit your broadcast time slot - including commercial breaks.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我们专利的“舞台经理”软件让你的演出保持流程顺畅，并能优化时长契合你的节目档期—广告时段也考虑在内。
(埃德温)\\\\我们的系统绝不会让你头疼，没有任何麻烦。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Please continue into the Lobby and take a seat.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\请继续进入大厅并随意入座。
(埃德温)\\\\拜托。
(埃德温)\\\\求你了……快叫人来帮忙……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Project update.  I figured it out. There's a leak.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\项目最新进展。我查明原因了—有泄漏。
(埃德温)\\\\录音中……测试，测试，音量正常。
(埃德温)\\\\护士多莉，请说声“你好”。
(埃德温)\\\\说点什么，是我，埃德温。完毕。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Seat filler audience included at additional cost.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\需要补位观众的话，要额外付费。
(埃德温)\\\\把频率设置为4625……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Simply interact with the performance by shooting targets to progress the story.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\只要射击目标，就能和表演互动，推动剧情发展。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Simply supply the "Stage Manager" with the desired character names, location, and genre.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\只需告知“舞台经理”你想要的角色名字、地点和剧本类型即可。
(埃德温)\\\\那么，你愿意嫁给我吗？拜托了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Someone told them about M2. Well, they can't have it.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\有人把M2的事透露给他们了。但他们绝对得不到它。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Stop talking like her. You’re not her. I never want to hear or even think about you ever again. Ever!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\别再学她说话了，你不是她。我再也不想听到你，甚至不想再想起你，永远！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Test test... journal entry. I got the change order from Hen last night.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\测试，测试……日志记录。我昨晚收到亨利的更改单了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\That’s great! Do you mind if I record you for a test?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\太棒了！我能录一下你的声音做个测试吗？
(埃德温)\\\\没错！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The MCM Studio comes equipped with automated cameras, props and lights.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\MCM工作室配备了自动摄像机、道具和灯光。
(埃德温)\\\\MCM设施暂时关闭。
(埃德温)\\\\MCM工坊暂时关闭。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The bear saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it scared the Bear and he ran away!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那只熊看到大家吵成一团！人们大喊大叫、咬牙切齿，把熊吓得赶紧跑开了！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The bouncy blue bunny hopped through the forest down to the garden patch.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\蹦蹦跳跳的蓝色兔子穿过森林，来到菜园。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The bunny saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it scared the bunny and he ran away!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\兔子看到大家吵成一团！人们大喊大叫、咬牙切齿，把兔子吓得撒腿就跑！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The chicken saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it scared the chicken and she ran away!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\小鸡看到大家吵成一团！人们大喊大叫、咬牙切齿，把小鸡吓得飞快跑开了！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The clumsy chicken danced in the sunlight on top of her coop.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那只笨拙的母鸡在鸡舍顶上，阳光下跳着舞。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The company is going to collapse and they’re all going to hate me.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\公司快垮了，他们都会怨恨我。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The fox saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it scared the fox and he ran away!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那只狐狸看到大家吵成一团！人们大喊大叫、咬牙切齿，把狐狸吓得拼命逃跑！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The gator saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it scared the gator and he ran away!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\鳄鱼看到大家在吵架！人群大声喊叫、咬牙切齿，把鳄鱼吓坏了，他撒腿就跑！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The loading dock is like two hundred feet away, and there's a fence and everything.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\装卸区大概有两百英尺远，还有栅栏什么的隔着。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The message will be recorded on a tape drive so that I can listen to it when I get back to my desk on the other side of the building.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我要把这条消息录到磁带驱动器里，这样等我回到大楼另一头的办公桌时就能听到了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The money is gone. I just need to finish the new Fazbear project, and then everyone will come back. We can get back to normal.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\钱已经没了。我只要把新的费斯熊项目做完，大家就会愿意回来。我们一切就会恢复正常。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The moral of the story is that friendship is the real treasure.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这个故事告诉我们，友谊才是真正的财富。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\The pesky puppy saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it scared the puppy and she ran away!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那只烦人的小狗看到大家在吵架！人群大声叫喊、咬牙切齿，把小狗吓得她逃跑了！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Then a crafty fox sat down and started a game of chess.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\接着，一只狡猾的狐狸坐下来，开始下一盘棋。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Then boy, have we got some news for you! Welcome to the MCM television studio of the future.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\伙计，我们可有好消息告诉你！欢迎来到未来的MCM电视演播厅！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Then the crafty fox came over and challenged all of them to a race, but he cheated to win!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\随后，那只狡猾的狐狸过来，向大家发起了一场赛跑挑战，但他耍赖赢了！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\They all started a band and lived happily ever after. The End.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\他们后来一起组了乐队，从此幸福快乐地生活在一起。故事结束。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\They had so much fun! Do you remember what happens next?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\他们玩得真开心！你还记得接下来发生了什么吗？

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Think of it as your new babysitter. But it doesn’t get paid and go home. It’ll stay with us and help around the house.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\就把它当作你新的保姆吧，不过它既不领工资，也不会回家。它会一直陪着我们，帮我们做家务。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This Example Show is written and performed by a single costumed writer-director-cameraman-puppeteer-producer in front of an automated studio audience.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这个例子节目是由一位身兼编剧、导演、摄像、木偶师和制片人的演员在全自动演播厅观众面前独自创作并表演的。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This client tour will show you just what I’m capable of… get ready to be amazed.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这次客户参观会让你见识到我的本事……准备好大吃一惊吧。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This is great! He’s gonna love it!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\太棒了！他一定会喜欢的！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This is it. This is the one. Bigger than the Clean-o-Vac!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\就是它。这就是我要找的！比Clean-o-Vac还要厉害！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This is it. This is the one. Bigger than the Clean-o-Vac!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\就是它。这就是我要找的！比Clean-o-Vac还要厉害！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This is the last project I ever do for them.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这是我为他们做的最后一个项目了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This is where I heard it. It's her, or someone that sounds like her.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我就是在这里听到的。是她，或者是个声音和她很像的人。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This might be a little awkward, but I have something very important to ask you.\\\\Okay? Here goes.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这可能有点尴尬，但我有件非常重要的事情想问你。\\\\好吧？我要开口了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\This shocked all the friends and they realized that anger didn’t solve anything.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\这件事让所有朋友都大吃一惊，他们也明白了，发怒并不能解决任何问题。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Those useless things are then used to create NEW midway\\\\games, costumes and technologies for\\\\your family fun centers at a discounted price!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\那些原本没用的东西随后会被用来打造全新的嘉年华游戏、服饰和技术，\\\\为您的家庭娱乐中心带来更多乐趣，价格还很实惠！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\To explain how it all works, I would like to introduce one of our many hard working recycling auto-mations.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\为了解释整个流程，我要请出我们众多勤奋工作的自动回收机器人之一。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Ugh! How am I supposed to tell David that his mother is gone? How am I supposed to raise a kid on my own? His life is ruined… My life is ruined.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\唉！我该怎么跟大卫说他妈妈不在了？我又怎么能一个人把孩子养大？他的生活全毁了……我的人生也完了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Uh... If yes, I have a ring to give you later. It's somewhere around here.\\\\And leave a response at the sound of the beep...
column3: (埃德温)\\\\呃……如果你的答案是肯定的，等会儿我有一枚戒指要给你，就在附近。\\\\请在听到提示音后留言……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\We just 'click' in every way. I hope you feel the same.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我们各方面都很合拍。我希望你也有这种感觉。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\We've known each other for how long now?\\\\I don't remember your start date off the top of my head, but it's been a few.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\咱们认识多久了？\\\\我一时半会儿想不起你入职的具体日期，但也有一阵子了。
(埃德温)\\\\欢迎各位潜在的投资人和买家。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Welcome to Bed Time. Would you like a story to help you sleep?
column3: (埃德温)\\\\欢迎来到“睡前时光”。需要个故事助眠吗？
(埃德温)\\\\欢迎来到全球首家“回收中心”。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Welcome, potential buyers, to Edwin Murray's Costume Manor - the leading powerhouse\\\\in costumed entertainment and carnival game technologies. Woo.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\欢迎各位潜在买家来到埃德温·默里的服装庄园—致力于套装娱乐和嘉年华游戏科技的行业领跑者。呜呼！
(埃德温)\\\\那“天赋”呢？我们把“天赋”去掉了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\What the hell was that? They treat me like some contractor to crack a whip at.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\刚才那是怎么回事？他们把我当成随叫随到的临时工一样对待。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Who am I kidding, you’re not really you! Ugh, I’ve been so stupid.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\我在骗谁啊，你根本就不是你自己！唉，我真是太蠢了。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Why did you go? You weren’t even supposed to be there. You were supposed to be here with me and David.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你为什么要走？你本来就不该在那里，你应该和我，还有大卫，一起在这里。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Why would they change them now? Are they pulling my leg? The new concepts are frankly creepy.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\他们现在为什么要更换？是在逗我玩吗？这些新点子说实话有点渗人。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\With the MCM Tele-puppet system, a single costumed owner.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\有了MCM遥控木偶系统，只需一个穿着戏服的操控者……

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\Wow, Fiona! He turned out great! I think it’s your best one yet. David, David, look at this. Look look.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\太棒了，菲奥娜！他真的做得很出色！我觉得这是你做得最棒的一个了。大卫，大卫，快看这个。快看快看！
(埃德温)\\\\嗯嗯嗯。
(埃德温)\\\\好，好，好。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\You know, the MCM wouldn't be this successful without you.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你知道，如果没有你，MCM根本不会这么成功。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\You've become the heart of the company and I want to share it with you.
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你已经成了这家公司的核心，我想和你一起分享这一切。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\You. You! I let a machine raise my kid. You’re not real. What was I thinking?!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你……你！我竟然让一台机器养大了我的孩子。你根本不是真的。我当时到底在想什么？！
(埃德温)\\\\你的爸爸妈妈都很爱你。晚安。

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\You’re cold. Getting hotter… Hotter… You’re burning up!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\你现在很冷……越来越热……更热了……你都快被找到了！

column2: (EDWIN)\\\\…Stop. You're not him. You're not! Stop sounding like him!
column3: (埃德温)\\\\……停下。你不是他，不是！别再学他说话了！
(大象)\\\\(一边追玩家一边咯咯笑)
(大象)\\\\凉啦凉啦……

column2: (ELEPHANT)\\\\Dum de dum de dum de dum…
column3: (大象)\\\\咚咚咚咚咚咚—
(大象)\\\\哎呀！！有只老鼠！
(大象)\\\\费-菲-福-迪利-范！！
(大象)\\\\呵呵呵！
(大象)\\\\我快要烧起来啦！
(大象)\\\\我要倒在你身上了！

column2: (ELEPHANT)\\\\Now, what was I looking for? I forget.
column3: (大象)\\\\咦，我刚才要找什么来着？忘记啦。
(大象)\\\\嘘……我闻到味道了。
(大象)\\\\找到你啦！
(大象)\\\\越来越热啦，越来越热—

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\Disenage emergency brake, leave the elevator, and return to the maintenance box.
column3: (电梯)\\\\解开紧急刹车，离开电梯，回到维修箱。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\Look for a damaged gear and replace it with the corresponding replacement part.
column3: (电梯)\\\\找到损坏的齿轮，用匹配的零件把它换上。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\Now that the obstructive object has been removed, rotate the handcrank to pull the elevator up.
column3: (电梯)\\\\障碍物已清理后，旋转手摇把，把电梯升上去。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\Once the elevator is off, please remove the object causing the obstruction from the elevator machinery.
column3: (电梯)\\\\当电梯停止，务必把导致堵塞的东西从电梯机械里取出来。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\Press the open hatch button and proceed under the elevator.
column3: (电梯)\\\\按下开舱口按钮，然后走到电梯底下。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\Press the red button labeled close hatch and crank the elevator back to its original\\\\position. Next, turn on the elevator and close the repair.
column3: (电梯)\\\\按下红色的“关闭舱口”按钮，再把电梯摇回原来的位置。最后，重新开启电梯，完成修理。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\The emergency brake lever must be in the down position before any repairs in the maitenance hatch.
column3: (电梯)\\\\进行维修舱口修理前，必须先把紧急刹车杆拉到下方位置。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\This audio tape provides instructions on what to do if an obstruction becomes lodged within the drive motor of an\\\\elevator. You will be guided on how to safely and efficently remove the obstruction and restart the\\\\elevator. First, please pull the level next to the maintenance box down to open it.
column3: (电梯)\\\\本录音带将为您讲解当有异物卡在电梯驱动马达时应如何处理。您将获指导，学习如何安全且高效地清除障碍物，并让电梯重新运行。首先，请下拉维修箱旁的杠杆，将其开启。

column2: (ELEVATOR)\\\\To start the automatic software diagnoses and repair, press the colored buttons in the following order: 3,1,4,2
column3: (电梯)\\\\要启动自动化的软件检测与修复流程，请按下彩色按钮，顺序为：3，1，4，2。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\But I miss my child more.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\但我更想念我的孩子。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\But would you consider visiting every once in a while?
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\你会愿意偶尔回来看看吗？

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\But, the company doesn’t matter any more. It’s over.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\不过公司现在已经无关紧要了，这一切都结束了。
(F10 N4)\\\\进入待机模式……

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\He can help finish the program…
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\他可以帮忙完成这个项目……

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\I am sending you a technician. He has your M2 blueprints\\\\as well as executive access.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\我正派一位技术员过去。他手上有你的M2蓝图和最高管理权限。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\I beg you. Put it all aside and fix M2. It is not too late.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\我请求你，请把一切放下，修好M2。现在还来得及。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\I hope you’re taking care of yourself.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\希望你能好好照顾自己。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\I watched him grow up… Through this machine. I want him back.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\我看着他长大……都是通过这台机器。我真的希望他能回来。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\It has done many bad things. No one who enters the MCM is safe.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\它做过许多可怕的事情。进入MCM的人都不安全。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\It wasn’t me. It was different.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\不是我，那时的状况不一样。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\It will no longer listen. It mimics rage.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\它已经无法再听从命令了，只是在模仿愤怒。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\It’s been a long time since we had a chance to talk.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\我们已经很久没有好好谈话了。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\It’s not too late to fix our family.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\我们还有机会挽回这个家。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\Knowing you, you are still trying to hold it all together.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\我了解你，你总在苦苦支撑着一切。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\M2 can no longer be controlled.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\M2已经彻底失控了。
(F10 N4)\\\\请你再考虑一下，把这个程序完成吧。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\Somehow, it has been damaged and is malfunctioning.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\不知怎么地，它已经损坏并开始出现故障。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\While the M2 began as a copy of my program\\\\I believe it can become something more…
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\M2虽然起初只是我的程序的一个复制品\\\\但我相信，它完全可以成就更多……

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\You can stay up in the main house, if you want to.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\如果你愿意，可以去主屋住。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\You give me no other option.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\你没有留给我其他选择。

column2: (F10 N4)\\\\You need to let it go.
column3: (F10 N4)\\\\你得学会放下了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\ Great. Now that I assume you are done with the alignment, use the diagnosis and repair function.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\很好。既然我猜你已经完成了校准，那就用诊断和修复功能吧。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A bunny hopped over and offered to play cards.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只小兔子跳过来，邀请大家一起玩牌。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A bunny hopped over and offered to play cards. But they\\\\couldn’t agree on the game. The bunny was sad.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\小兔子想玩牌，可他们一直没法决定玩哪种游戏。兔子有点难过了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A clumsy chicken came and spilled her marbles. They had fun picking them up.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只笨拙的小母鸡跑来，不小心把弹珠撒了一地。他们一起捡弹珠，玩得非常开心。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A clumsy chicken joined them and they went out for ice cream but she dropped all their ice cream! Oh no!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\笨拙的小母鸡一起加入了大家，大家出去吃冰淇淋，结果她把所有人的冰淇淋都掉在了地上！糟糕！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A pesky little puppy yapped and played fetch.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只顽皮的小狗汪汪叫着，和大家玩抛接球。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A pesky puppy played fetch by itself on the beach.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只调皮的小狗自己在沙滩上玩起了捡球。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A pesky puppy yipped and yapped. She made so much noise\\\\that she gave everyone a headache.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\小狗叫个没完，闹腾得让大家头都疼了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A roly poly bear joined the others and offered his honey.\\\\But then he spilled it all over them. Oh no!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只圆滚滚的小熊加入进来，捧出他的蜂蜜，结果不小心全倒在大家身上了。糟糕！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A roly poly bear sat down and offered a pot of honey. They ate with glee.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\圆滚滚的小熊坐下来，拿出一罐蜂蜜，大家一起开心地品尝。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A rumbly tumbly bear sang sweetly by a big blue lake.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只胖胖的熊挨着蓝色大湖，愉快地唱着歌。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\A wily fox buckled swashes in his pirate ship.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只狡猾的狐狸在自己的海盗船上大展身手，扮起了海盗冒险。
(菲奥娜)\\\\一切都还好吗？希望你没问题。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\An angry alligator came by and promised not to eat anyone. They had carrots instead.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只愤怒的鳄鱼路过，说不会吃任何人。于是大家改吃胡萝卜了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\An angry alligator came by and promised not to eat anyone.\\\\But then he ate one of them.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\愤怒的鳄鱼保证不吃任何人，但最后还是把其中一个给吃掉了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\An angry alligator was swimming in the lake.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一只生气的鳄鱼在湖里游来游去。
(菲奥娜)\\\\现在，你就在这里。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\And if all goes well, this is an opportunity to reflect and appreciate the people in their lives who matter most.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果一切顺利，就能够借此机会，回顾并珍惜身边最重要的人。
(菲奥娜)\\\\而且，请记住……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\As for the elevator, it’s just a bunch of Ed’s chicken scratches…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\至于电梯，那其实就是埃德的一堆乱七八糟的涂鸦……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Because, you’re in the elevator as well. Which is still good. But less good.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\毕竟，你现在也在电梯里。这当然还不错，但就没原来那么好了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\再造一个吧。
(菲奥娜)\\\\把舱门关上。
(菲奥娜)\\\\把舱门关上。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Close the hatch. Reset the crank. Turn on the power and you are done.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\关上舱门，重设摇柄，接通电源，搞定。
(菲奥娜)\\\\出来吧。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Come out, come out wherever you are.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\出来吧，别躲着，无论你在哪儿。
(菲奥娜)\\\\大卫？大卫去哪了？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Despite the circumstance, it is nice to meet you face to face.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\虽然情况特殊，但能和你面对面见面还是挺高兴的。
(菲奥娜)\\\\别推我。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Don’t be mad. We’ll talk when I’m back next week.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\别生气，下周我回来再和你说。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, I hate talking to you through this stupid bear, but it’s hard to reach you otherwise…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，我真是不想用这只笨熊跟你说话，可是好像也只能这样才能联系到你……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, I hope this message reaches you as soon as you get a break.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，希望你一有空就能看到这条消息。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, I really don’t want to leave things like this.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，我真的不想让事情一直这样僵着。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, honey, how are you holding up? I just heard the news.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，亲爱的，你还好吗？我刚听说消息。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, honey, how are you holding up? I just heard the news.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，亲爱的，你现在哪还撑得住吗？我刚刚听到消息。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, you'll figure it out. Just take a deep breath.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，你会想明白的，先深呼吸一下。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, you’ll figure it out. Just take a deep breath.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，你会想明白的，先深呼吸一下。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Ed, you’re not going to want to hear this, but there‘s\\\\a lot of grumbling on the work floor.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德，这话你可能不爱听，可是工作区里现在怨声载道。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Edwin abandoned us. He shut himself away in our home.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德温把我们都扔下了，把自己关在家里。
(菲奥娜)\\\\埃德温！埃德！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Edwin, calm down and give it some thought. Try again. Make another and we can all be together.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德温，冷静点，仔细想想，重新试一次。只要再造一个，我们就能团聚了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Edwin, it doesn’t make sense. It’s terrible and there’s no logic behind it.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德温，这根本说不通，太糟糕了，完全没有任何道理。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Edwin, you can’t put it off any longer.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\埃德温，你不能再拖下去了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\埃德温，你得听我说。
(菲奥娜)\\\\仅限员工进入。
(菲奥娜)\\\\切换到待机模式。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\First, open the ‘repair-matic’ box. Oh. It may already be open. But if it isn’t, then do that.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\首先，打开“维修宝”工具箱。哦，可能已经开了，如果还没开，就先打开。
(菲奥娜)\\\\快出来，别错过了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\太好了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Happy birthday, Sweetie. Mommy made this special for you.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\生日快乐，宝贝。妈妈专门为你做的哦。
(菲奥娜)\\\\生日快乐，宝贝。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Head to the main house and activate the communications sub-terminal.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\去主屋，启动通信分控台。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Hello, Employee, if you're listening to this tape, the elevator has once again stopped working.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你好，员工，如果你能听到这盘录音，说明电梯又一次坏掉了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Hello, Employee. From the bottom of our hearts, Ed and\\\\ I apologize for all the elevator problems.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你好，员工。我们由衷地为所有电梯的问题向你道歉—埃德和我都是。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Hey rider. There is too much weight in the elevator.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\嘿，乘客，电梯超重了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\等一下，还有人没到。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Hopefully, anyone trapped inside is able to climb out between floors.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\希望困在里面的人能趁电梯卡在两层之间的时候爬出来。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\How are you supposed to increase the speed?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你打算怎么让速度变快？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\How? I see you at the door.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\怎么？我看到你已经走到门口了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\我的电量快耗尽了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\我是来帮忙的。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I am not here to shame. Just trying to help you fix the lift.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我不是来责怪你，只是想帮你修好电梯。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I baked it myself… for David’s special day.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我自己亲手烤的蛋糕……为大卫的特别日子准备的。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I don’t want to argue anymore. I made my\\\\decision and I have to go… just for a few days\\\\until the installation is finished.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我不想再争了。我已经决定了，我得走几天……等安装完毕就回来。
(菲奥娜)\\\\我有句话要转达给他。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I have to go help the Fall Fest crew… just for a few days until the installation is finished.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我得去帮秋季节的团队……只离开几天，等安装好就回来。
(菲奥娜)\\\\我听见你了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\希望这样能奏效。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I know you are excited, but you can’t let them know about me.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我知道你很激动，但别让他们发现我的存在。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I remember you are supposed to use the emergency brake\\\\then turn off the elevator?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我记得你需要先拉紧急刹车，再关闭电梯？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I see right through your simple shell game.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你的小把戏瞒不过我。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I want you to know, this is not my fault. The instructions are that bad.\\\\Ed writes like a doctor...
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我想让你知道，这不是我的错，是说明书太烂了。埃德写字跟医生一样难认……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I will be downstairs when you need me.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你需要我的时候，我会在楼下。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If all went well, the elevator should start moving again.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果一切顺利，电梯就该重新启动了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If anything does go wrong, we want you to know that it’s not your fault.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果真的出什么差错，我们想让你知道这不是你的责任。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If not, tell them not to worry and to lie flat on their backs and grab the side walls until repairs are finished.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果没有，让他们别担心，平躺下来、抓住侧壁，等修好为止。
(菲奥娜)\\\\如果还是不行……也请安心。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you are personally worried about weight issues,\\\\I suggest a good diet and exercise.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果你自己担心体重问题，\\\\我建议你注意饮食并多锻炼。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you are successful, let me be the first to congratulate you.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果你成功了，那就让我第一个祝贺你。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you behave, you can have your tiger.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果你乖的话，你就能得到你的老虎。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you could change anything you wanted, what would it be?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果你能随意改变一件事，那你会选什么？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you could change anything you wanted, what would it be?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果让你改变任何你想改变的事情，你会选什么？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you do not, M2 will never stop pursuing you.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\如果你不这么做，M2就会一直追着你不放。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\If you don’t come out, you won’t get your story.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你要是不出来，你就得不到你的故事。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Input the following code using the buttons.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\请用按钮输入以下代码。
(菲奥娜)\\\\大卫在躲着吗？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Isn’t that nice! So what happens next?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\挺不错的嘛！那接下来会发生什么？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It also would be a good time to ask the passengers if they have any messages for their loved ones, just in case.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\现在也是问问乘客们有没有什么话想对亲人说的好时机，以防万一。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It happened and you have to deal with it.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这事已经发生了，你只能去面对。
(菲奥娜)\\\\这里很孤单。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It knows what you want better than you do.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\它比你自己还更懂你想要什么。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It's your company now. Your dad believed in you. Otherwise, he wouldn't have left it to you.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\现在公司是你的了。你爸爸相信你，否则他不会把公司留给你。
(菲奥娜)\\\\它一直在看着。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It’s another one of life’s speed bumps. Don’t let it bring you down and think of it as a learning experience…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这也就是人生路上的又一个坎。别让它把你打倒，把它当做一次学习的机会……
(菲奥娜)\\\\宝贝，该睡觉了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It’s hard to explain… I just have this terrible feeling like I need to be there so nothing goes wrong… Just in case.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\说不太清……我只是有种很不好的预感，总觉得我必须在那里，这样才不会出意外……只是以防万一。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It’s hard to explain… I just have this terrible feeling like\\\\I need to be there so nothing goes wrong.\\\\Just in case.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这很难解释……我就是有种很糟糕的预感，\\\\觉得必须得在场，事情才不会出岔子。\\\\只为以防万一。
(菲奥娜)\\\\这里不安全。他们不会理解的。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\It’s your company now. Your dad believed in you. Otherwise, he wouldn’t have left it to you.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\现在公司是你的了。你爸爸相信你，否则他也不会把公司留给你。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I’m worried about the new suit design.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我对新款套装的设计还有点担心。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\I’ve never seen one like that before.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我之前从没见过那种款式。
(菲奥娜)\\\\这件事先只我们知道就好。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Make sure the emergency brake is engaged.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\一定要把紧急刹车拉好。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Morning. Did you stay up all night?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\早啊，你昨晚是不是一夜没睡？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\My communications with Edwin have been severed.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我和埃德温已经失去联系了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Next, rebalance the elevator. That’s it? No details? Ugh…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\接下来，调整电梯的平衡。就这些？没有具体步骤吗？哎……
(菲奥娜)\\\\接下来，关闭电梯电源。
(菲奥娜)\\\\禁止入内。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\No. “Latte”. It’s new. From Murray’s. Try it.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\不是，是“拿铁”。新口味，默里的店做的。尝一尝吧。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Now disengage the emergency break and back out carefully.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\现在松开紧急刹车，然后慢慢倒出去，小心点。
(菲奥娜)\\\\好了，现在该睡觉了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Now, let me check. …This is so disorganized.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\让我检查一下……这也太乱了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\现在，把电梯电源关掉。
(菲奥娜)\\\\没问题。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Oh no! That’s not how the story went!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\糟了！故事不是这样讲的！
(菲奥娜)\\\\糟了！他们这是干了什么？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Oh yeah. If you need to hear an instruction again, push the replay button on the tape recorder.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\对了，如果你需要再听一遍指令，就按录音机上的重播键。
(菲奥娜)\\\\亲爱的，你把他给吓坏了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Oh, right! You need to realign the elevator using the “realignment thingie”.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\噢，对了！你需要用“校准装置”重新对齐电梯。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Oh. There’s a note here. If the elevator is out of alignment, adjust the thing that balances it. That’s what it says…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\噢，这儿有张纸条。电梯没对齐的时候，调整平衡用的那个东西。字条上就是这么写的……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Oh. Well, yes. I used to be.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\噢，没错，我以前是的。
(菲奥娜)\\\\噢……对了，我说到哪儿了……
(菲奥娜)\\\\好吧！那我们直接进去。
(菲奥娜)\\\\好吧，那么……
(菲奥娜)\\\\好了？那我们开始吧。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Okay. Start the diagnostics routine by inputting the following code…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\请通过输入以下代码启动诊断程序……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Once the elevator is off, remove any obstructions from the exposed machinery.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\电梯关掉以后，把所有阻碍物清理出暴露的机械部位。
(菲奥娜)\\\\从前，从前……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Once you figured that part out, power on the elevator, disengage the emergency brake\\\\and cross your fingers…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\等你搞明白这一步，开机，松开紧急刹车，祈祷一切顺利……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\One of my costumers, Vic, nearly lost his hand today.\\\\All he did was spill a can of pop and the thing snapped shut like a bear trap.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我的一个顾客维克，今天差点手都没了。\\他不过是洒了罐汽水，结果那玩意儿一下子像捕兽夹似的合上了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Oop! Hold up! I almost forgot. Make sure the emergency brake is on before attempting any repair.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\哦，等等！差点忘了。维修前一定要先拉好紧急刹车。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Please follow these simple instructions to reset the elevator.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\请按以下简单操作步骤重置电梯。
(菲奥娜)\\\\请查一下这个情况。
(菲奥娜)\\\\请按下“开启维修舱门”按钮。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Push the green button to open the hatch.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\按下绿色按钮，就能打开舱门。
(菲奥娜)\\\\准备好迈出这一步了吗？
(菲奥娜)\\\\把曲柄复位吧。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\So you want to record me with that? What is it?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你想用那个东西来录我吗？那是什么呀？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\So, that part’s crystal clear, but I can’t read the next bit at all.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这部分我已经完全明白了，可后面那段我怎么看都看不清。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\So, there is some good news and some less good news.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\有好消息，不过也有些不太好的消息。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Sorry about that, elevator people. I’ll do a new recording\\\\when I get back from the Fall Fest installation next week.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\电梯那边的各位，不好意思啦。我下周秋季节布展回来后会重新录一份的。
(菲奥娜)\\\\马上停下你正在做的事。
(菲奥娜)\\\\帮我告诉埃德温—我依然爱他。
(菲奥娜)\\\\这就是我唯一的心愿。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That's great Honey, but you're missing the party...
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你做得很好，亲爱的，可是你正好错过了聚会……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That’s Murray’s secret recipe. The Stay Up Latte creates the perfect cup of coffee suited to you, based on your coffee habits.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这是默里的独家秘方。“熬夜拿铁”会根据你的咖啡习惯，为你量身定制一杯最适合你的完美咖啡。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That’s a great name. And I would be delighted to help. What kind of voice should I do?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这个名字真不错。我很乐意帮忙！你想让我用什么样的声音录制呢？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That’s great, Honey, but you’re missing the party.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你很棒，亲爱的，可是聚会你没赶上哦。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That’s great, Honey, but you’re missing the party.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你做得真好，亲爱的，可你已经错过聚会啦。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That’s incredible. What do you call it?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\太棒了！这个叫什么名字？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\That’s not the point. We have guests.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\问题不在这里，我们还有客人在呢。
(菲奥娜)\\\\没错，就是这样！
(菲奥娜)\\\\这就是默里独特的地方。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The bear saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth\\\\and it scared the Bear and he ran away!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\那只熊看到大家吵得不可开交！大家又喊又咬牙，吓得熊转身就跑了！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The bouncy blue bunny hopped through the forest down to the garden patch.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\那只活泼的蓝兔子蹦蹦跳跳地穿过森林，来到了菜园边。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The bunny saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their teeth and it\\\\scared the bunny and he ran away!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\兔子看到大家在吵架！大家又喊又咬牙，把兔子吓得撒腿跑开了！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The chicken saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their\\\\teeth and it scared the chicken and she ran away!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\那只小母鸡看到大家闹成一团！大家又叫又咬牙，吓得她扑棱棱地跑了！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The clumsy chicken danced in the sunlight on top of her coop.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\那只笨笨的小母鸡在自家鸡舍顶上沐浴着阳光跳起了舞。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The fox saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their\\\\teeth and it scared the fox and he ran away!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\狐狸看到大家都在争吵！大家吼叫着、咬牙切齿，把狐狸吓得跑掉了！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The gator saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their\\\\teeth and it scared the gator and he ran away!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\鳄鱼看到大家都在争吵！大家吼叫着、咬牙切齿，把鳄鱼吓得逃走了！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The good news is that you can make repairs from inside the elevator.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\好消息是，你可以在电梯里面完成修理。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The less good news is that you won’t have the lives of your fellow employees\\\\weighing on your conscience if things take a downward turn.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\不太好的消息是，如果情况恶化，也不用背负同事们的命运在良心上。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The moral of the story is that friendship is the real treasure.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这个故事的寓意是：真正的宝藏是友谊。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\The puppy saw everyone arguing! The group yelled and gnashed their\\\\teeth and it scared the puppy and she ran away!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\小狗看到大家都在争吵！大家吼叫着、咬牙切齿，把小狗吓跑了！

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Then a crafty fox sat down and started a game of chess.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\然后，一只狡猾的狐狸坐下来开始下棋。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Then the crafty fox came over and challenged all of them to a race, but he cheated to win!
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\接着，那只狡猾的狐狸跑过来，向大家发起赛跑挑战，但他耍赖赢了！
(菲奥娜)\\\\你在这里啊。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\They all started a band and lived happily ever after. The End.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\他们一起组了乐队，从此幸福快乐地生活在一起。故事结束。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\They had so much fun! Do you remember what happens next?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\他们玩得那么开心！你还记得接下来发生了什么吗？
(菲奥娜)\\\\此区域禁止进入。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\This shocked all the friends and they realized that anger didn’t solve anything.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\这一切让朋友们大吃一惊，他们也明白了，发火根本解决不了问题。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\To re-lign the elevator, use the sliders to rebalance the load weight alignment… doohicky.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\要重新调整电梯，请用滑块重新平衡载重……那啥玩意来着。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Trisha will babysit David while I’m gone. I love you both and I’ll be back next week.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\特丽莎会在我走的时候照看大卫。我爱你们，等我下周回来。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Try tofu. You would be surprised at how it soaks in flavors…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\试试豆腐吧。你会惊讶它有多能入味……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Turn on the elevator and disengage the emergency brake.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\启动电梯并松开紧急刹车。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Turn on the power and you are done.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\打开电源，就搞定啦。
(菲奥娜)\\\\观看学习。
(菲奥娜)\\\\我们可以一起修好它。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\We can’t start the story without the bedtime boy.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\没有你，我们可没法开始讲故事呢。
(菲奥娜)\\\\我们爱你。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\We must convince him to repair M2.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\我们得说服他去修M2。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Welcome to Bed Time. Would you like a story to help you sleep?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\欢迎来到睡前时间。你要不要听个故事助眠呢？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Well, how would you describe it in one word?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\那你会用一个词怎么形容它呢？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Well, hurry up. We’re doing cake in five minutes with or without you.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\好了，快点。五分钟后我们就要切蛋糕了，不管你来不来。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Well, it can’t be that different from the other elevator instructions,\\\\so let’s give it a shot.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\嗯，这应该跟其他电梯操作说明差不多，\\\\那我们来试试看吧。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\What for? I don’t even know you. I’m brand new here. Let’s start again. I'm Fiona. And you are?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\为什么？我连你是谁都不知道。我是新来的。我们重新认识一下吧。我叫菲奥娜。你呢？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\When that’s done, increase the speed of the elevator to\\\\accommodate for any changes in carrying weight.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\等这一步完成后，调高电梯速度，\\\\以适应载重量的变化。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\When the machinery is clear of debris, rotate the hand crank clock-wise to raise the elevator.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\清理完机器里的杂物后，顺时针转动手摇柄，把电梯升起来。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\When the rebalancing is complete, open the elevator doors.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\平衡调整完成后，就可以打开电梯门了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\你去哪儿了？
(菲奥娜)\\\\你是哪一个？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Why are you trying to come in here?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你为什么要进来这里？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Why are you trying to come in here?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你为什么要进来这里？

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Why sleep when you can “Stay Up Latte”?
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\为什么要睡觉？你可以来杯“熬夜拿铁”呀。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Without power, you will trap us both down here in the dark.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\没有电的话，你会把我们俩困在这里的黑暗里。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You are now safe to close everything up.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\现在可以安全地关上所有设备了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You are now safe to get under the elevator.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\现在你可以放心地进入电梯底下了。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You can fix it as a team and no one person is to blame.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\大家合作就能修好，没有人需要独自负责。
(菲奥娜)\\\\你依然还有用处。
(菲奥娜)\\\\你骗不了我。
(菲奥娜)\\\\你以前做到过。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You do not mean that. It is me. I’m Fiona.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你不是这个意思。这是我，我是菲奥娜。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You don’t have to wait around until someone notices that it’s stuck and fixes it.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你无需等别人发现电梯卡住再修，自己就能动手解决。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You have a lot of new ideas and new projects coming in, but the staff\\\\can’t keep up with all your changes.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你不断有新想法新项目，但员工们\\\\跟不上你的变化。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You have questions, but there is no time.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你有问题想问，但我们没时间了。
(菲奥娜)\\\\你看上去好糟糕！
(菲奥娜)\\\\你得再试一次。
(菲奥娜)\\\\你让我们俩都陷入了危险……

column2: (FIONA)\\\\Your creative energy’s amazing and I love you for it…
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你的创造力真棒，我就是喜欢你这点……
(菲奥娜)\\\\你的爸爸妈妈爱你。晚安，做个好梦。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\You’re busy, but you can’t rush these things.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\你虽然很忙，但这些事情急不得。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\…I guess you’ll just figure that part out.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\……我想这部分你自会明白的。

column2: (FIONA)\\\\…but I think you need to step back a little and focus on one project at a time.
column3: (菲奥娜)\\\\……不过我觉得你该稍微停一停，一次专注做好一个项目。

column3: (KIT)\\\\霍斯！你真棒！你做到了！你帮船长找到了最完美的礼物！

column2: (M1)\\\\Hello, David. It is nice to meet you.
column3: (M1)\\\\你好，大卫。很高兴见到你。

column2: (M2)\\\\Ask your mom, if she’s not busy.
column3: (M2)\\\\要是你妈妈不忙的话，去问问她吧。

column3: (M2)\\\\我现在抽不开身，宝贝。明天我们一起玩点好玩的，我保证。

column2: (M2)\\\\Due to a minor… detonation, there is damage to my office interior\\\\as well as a small fire.
column3: (M2)\\\\由于一个小小的爆炸，我办公室内部有点受损，还起了一点点火。

column2: (M2)\\\\Note to self. A portable cleaner that gets rid of smoke damage…\\\\Better yet, a Clean-o-Vac attachment.

column2: ..software development and the entire MCM catalog. We would love to keep you on as a lead engineer. Although we now technically own the land, we would never touch the house your parents built. We feel this offer has been more than fair, considering how far behind you are. It's just too much for you to handle alone. We are waiting for your response.  - WA
column3: ……软件开发以及整个MCM的产品目录。我们很愿意让你继续担任首席工程师。虽然从法理上说我们现在拥有了这片土地，但你的父母盖的房子我们绝不会动。考虑到你目前的进度，这个提议已经非常公正了。你一个人真的应付不过来。我们正在等你的回复。—WA
