column2: Are they insane? The look of these new animatronics is Fiona's design and they're great. First they approve the art. Then they approve the proofs. Now, they change their minds when we're so close to final. Why would they change them now? Are they pulling my leg? The new concepts are frankly creepy. It doesn't matter... I'm  not changing a single bit of her work and they can't make me.
column3: 他们是不是疯了？这些新仿生人偶的造型是菲奥娜设计的，非常棒！他们先批了美术，接着批了样稿，现在马上就要定稿了却又变卦，为什么非要这个时候改？是耍我玩吗？说实话，这些新概念真的很诡异。但无所谓……我绝不会改动她的任何一点作品，他们也别想逼我。

column2: Attention. We're going to need everyone to come in this weekend. This is not optional. The party is on Saturday in the admin conference room 1. Don't tell David. It's a surprise.  - EM
column3: 请注意，本周末所有人都必须到场，无一例外。聚会定在周六，行政一号会议室。不要告诉大卫，这可是个惊喜。—EM

column2: Barb, I swear if I hear that song one more time I'm going to tear that Dollie off her hinges. I have no clue how much longer I can take it here.
column3: Barb，我发誓要是再听到那首歌一次，我就要把那个多莉从铰链上拆下来。我真的不知道自己还能在这里撑多久。

column2: Can someone please mark where we're supposed to go down there? Bob went down and I haven't seen him in days.
column3: 有谁能帮忙在我们应该下去的地方做个标记吗？Bob下去了，我已经好几天没见到他了。
奇卡的派对世界
机密

column2:
Dear MCM,

My husband is a steel worker, and recently he was moved to the night shift. He tried your "Stay Up Latte" and it worked wonders for about two weeks. He is now in the hospital because of your drink. You will be hearing from our lawyers soon. 

R. Quinn
column3:
亲爱的MCM：

我丈夫是钢铁工人，最近转到了夜班。他喝了你们的“熬夜拿铁”，头两个星期确实非常有效。但现在他因为这款饮料进了医院。很快你们就会接到我们律师的信。

R.奎恩

column2:
Dear Mr. Murray and Co., 

My child loves your Jest Cereal. However, the pranks inside are extremely inappropriate. The hand buzzer paralyzed  our dog Fido! We are never buying this cereal ever again.  

Sincerely, 
E. Guerrero
column3:
亲爱的默里先生及公司：

我的孩子很喜欢你们的Jest麦片，不过里面的恶作剧实在太不适合儿童了。电击器甚至把我们家的狗Fido给麻痹了！我们再也不会买这麦片了。

此致敬礼，
E.格雷罗

column2:
Dear Mr. Murray, 

I'm writing this to complain about my purchase of the Mushmen Music Machine. It learned my child's musical tastes, but it also imitated everything it heard! TV commercials, blenders, and even private conversations between my husband and me. I am returning it immediately. 

Sincerely, 
A. Dumas
column3:
亲爱的默里先生：

我写信是要投诉我买的蘑菇人音乐机。它学会了我孩子喜欢的音乐，但也模仿周围听到的所有声音！广告、搅拌机，甚至还有我和丈夫的私人谈话。我马上要把它退掉。

此致敬礼，
A.杜马斯

column2:
Dear Mr. Murray, 

We bought your Magic Coat Rack last May. It was an amazing addition to our home. But lately it seems to change size at random. One morning I came out to find all my coats flung across the room and the coat rack ten feet tall! Can you send us instructions on how to fix this? We're afraid someone might get hurt. 

Sincerely,
B. Wyatt
column3:
亲爱的默里先生：

我们去年五月买了你们的魔法衣架，起初真的很棒。但最近它会莫名其妙变大变小。有天早上我出来一看，所有外套都被甩到屋里，衣架竟然长到十英尺高！能否发给我们使用或修理说明？我们很担心会发生危险。

此致敬礼，
B.怀亚特

column2:
Dear Mr. Murray, Fiona is amazing. The client is very happy with her chicken designs. Their sales are through the roof. I just wish the costume looked a little bit more like Fiona's art... I'm worried about how it will work with kids. It gives me nightmares.  
- Milton
column3:
亲爱的默里先生，菲奥娜真是太棒了。客户对她设计的鸡形角色非常满意，销量节节攀升。我只是希望套装能更贴近菲奥娜画里的样子……我有点担心它跟小孩互动的反应。说实话，它老让我做噩梦。
-米尔顿

column2: Dear Mr. Murray. The returns are over flowing. The orders are drying up. Please advise.
column3: 默里先生，退货已经堆满了仓库，订单也越来越少。请指示该怎么办。

column2: Ed! How many times did I tell you? "Mycelium" only has one 'l'. Now, all the marketing images are misspelled. Our clients are going to think we make mistakes and don't pay attention to the details. Is there any way to fix it now?
column3: 埃德！我跟你重复过多少遍了？“Mycelium”只有一个‘l’。现在所有宣传图都拼错了。客户会觉得我们粗心大意。还有办法补救吗？

column2:
Edwin, I am sending you a technician. He has your M2 blueprints as well as executive access. While the M2 began as a copy of my program, I believe it can become something more. It wasn’t me. It was different. Somehow, it has been damaged and is malfunctioning. 

M2 can no longer be controlled. It will no longer listen. It mimics rage. It has done many bad things. No one who enters the MCM is safe.

Please reconsider. Finish the program.
column3:
埃德温，我已派技术员前往你处。他手里有你的M2蓝图，还有顶级权限。虽然M2最初只是我的程序的复制品，但我相信它可以超越原有形态。它不是我。它已经变了。某种原因让它受损并发生了故障。

M2已经无法控制了。它再也不会听话。它仿佛充满愤怒。它已经做了很多坏事。没有人进入MCM还能保证安全了。

请再想想，完成这个程序吧。

column2: Edwin, are we losing our home? I don't understand. Wasn't I good enough?
column3: 埃德温，我们是不是要失去我们的家了？我不明白，难道我还不够好吗？

column2: Edwin, please talk to me. We need to stop it together. Here are the blueprints for a "Cradle". It can keep David safe and provide boundaries. It's a type of computer, and it's bigger than anything you've done before. If you won't finish the program, consider building the cradle. It will keep people safe.
column3: 埃德温，求你和我说话。我们必须一起阻止它。这里有一个“摇篮”的设计图，它能让大卫安全，并设定必要的界限。它是一种计算机，比你以前做过的任何系统都要庞大。如果你不愿意完善那个程序，至少建造这个摇篮吧。这样大家才能安全。
能源配额

column2: Fiona, the new springlocks are working well, even with the water damage. They should be ready for the diner soon. I’ll just make sure to warn Hen about some of the more… odd behaviors they might have.
column3: 菲奥娜，新弹簧锁的效果很好，哪怕受过水浸都没问题。它们很快就能投入餐厅使用了。我会提醒Hen注意，有些……奇怪的行为可能会出现。

column2: Gary, I finally found the missing pieces of this stupid power device. Just got to head over there and turn the power on. I'll check in soon.
column3: 加里，我终于找到了这个该死的电源装置缺失的零件。马上就过去开机。很快再联系你。

column2: Great idea, Pete. Mr. Murray hasn't used these mailboxes for so long, it should be safe. I'd love to have some place for all of us to talk in private. I feel like the bossman is listening all the time... - Penny
column3: 好主意，皮特。默里先生这些信箱已经很久没用过了，应该很安全。我也很希望有个属于我们自己的私密交流空间。总觉得老板一直在监听我们的谈话……—佩妮
群聊#1
群聊#2
群聊#3
群聊#4
群聊#5
快乐花朵！
你听说菲奥娜的事了吗？

column2: Haven't seen Gary... I'm going to check the theatre. Found some films and I know he wanted to get the projector up and running..
column3: 还没见到加里……我要去剧场找找。发现了一些影片，我记得他很想让放映机重新运行起来……

column2: Haven't seen Gary... I'm going to check the theatre. Found some films and I know he wanted to get the projector up and running..
column3: 还没见到加里……我要去剧场找找。发现了一些影片，我记得他很想让放映机重新运行起来……

column2: Hello! Here is your mail for today: Your mailbox is full. Last mail received five weeks ago: Foreclosure Notice. Please Respond Immediately.
column3: 你好！以下是你今天的邮件：你的信箱已满。上次收到邮件是五周前：物业止赎通知。请尽快回复。

column2:
Hey Clarence, you as bored as I am? I can't believe we got the Retail Showroom detail again. So boring. 

Although did you finally get into the elevator? That thing hasn't worked in so long, I don't even think Murray knows what's down there anymore. - Shawn
column3:
喂，克拉伦斯，你是不是也跟我一样无聊？没想到我们又被分到零售展厅值班了，真是一点意思都没有。

对了，你后来终于进得去电梯了吗？那鬼东西坏了不知道多久，我觉得连默里都忘了楼下到底有些什么了。—肖恩

column2: Hey Penny, I’m going to change the first two digits to 01. Because I’m number 1! - Bob
column3: 嘿，佩妮，我要把前两个密码改成01。因为我是第一名！—鲍勃

column2: Hey everybody! Don’t tell Milton, but I figured out how to change the keycode to the conference room. I just added 300 to it, just to mess with him! - Bob
column3: 大家好！别告诉米尔顿哦，我已经搞清楚怎么改会议室的门码了，我干脆加了300上去，纯粹就是想捉弄他！—鲍勃

column2: Hey everyone. I was here late so I added another 300 to the code. Anyone have a camera when Milton tries to open it again! Priceless! - Bob
column3: 各位，我昨晚还留在公司，又把门码往上加了300。有人能拍下米尔顿下次开门时的表情吗？那一定精彩绝了！—鲍勃

column2: Hey everyone. These mail boxes are everywhere. If you see anything "strange" we can keep the group informed.  - Pete
column3: 大家注意，这里的信箱到处都是。如果你们发现什么“可疑”的事，记得随时让大家知道。—皮特

column2: Hey, I can't get the incinerator up and running. The chutes are getting clogged again. - Gary
column3: 唉，焚化炉我还是开不起来，投入口又堵住了。—加里

column2: Hey, I took Wally off this note. I changed the first two digits to 21, just because he’s such a jerk. I can’t wait to see his head explode. - Penny
column3: 喂，我把沃利从这张便条上划掉了，把前两个密码改成21，就因为他太讨人厌了。我已经等不及看他气炸的样子了。—佩妮

column2: Hey. Hey! Is anybody up there? I'm stuck down here! The elevator isn't working, and I'm getting really hungry. Is anyone getting this message?
column3: 喂，喂！有人在上面吗？我被困在下面了！电梯坏掉了，我快饿死了。有人能收到这条信息吗？
家。我的家。
我实在撑不下去了

column2: I heard it again this morning when I was down in R&D. Very clearly through one of the vents, it was Fiona's voice, I swear it on my mother's grave. I heard her and Edwin laughing and joking. Why would Edwin lie about Fall Fest? Did they fake her death for insurance money? I never did trust them.
column3: 今天早上我又在研发部听到了那个声音，很清楚地透过一个通风口传来，就是菲奥娜的声音，我敢对着我妈妈的坟墓发誓。我还听到她和埃德温在那嬉皮笑脸。为什么埃德温要对秋季节撒谎？他们是不是假死骗保险？我本来就不相信他们。

column2: I hope this message reaches someone. There's something outside. I have no idea what it wants, but I can still hear Thompson's screams.... I didn't sign up for this.
column3: 希望这条信息能被谁看到。外面有东西，我根本不知道它到底想干什么，但我还能听到汤普森的惨叫声……我可不是来受这个罪的。

column2: I just saw the code changed again. Anyone seen adjusting the code will be written up! - Milton
column3: 我又发现有人改了门码。任何被发现调整门码的人都要记入记录！—米尔顿

column2: I know, I know. I don't think it's that big of a problem. The misspelling actually helps us when it comes to possible copywrite issues. The double 'l' spelling protects us. Nobody will notice anyway.
column3: 我知道我知道。我觉得这不是啥大问题。其实拼写错了，反倒在处理版权问题时能保护我们。两个‘l’的写法就是咱们的保护伞。反正谁都发现不了。

column2: I stopped the show. I don't think there's another way in. I should be safe for now. A maniac in a costume chasing me. Like something out of a drive in movie. NO one is ever going to believe me. Just one guy or a whole group of psychos?
column3: 我把节目停了。我觉得没有其他路能进来。暂时应该安全了。一个穿着戏服的疯子在追我，简直就像汽车影院电影里的桥段。没人会信我。这只是一个人，还是一群疯子？

column2: I'm almost there. I can see the last permission upgrade. I'm going to get that Christmas Bonus, even if it kills me!
column3: 我快到了，已经能看到最后一道权限升级的界面了。哪怕拼了命，这次圣诞奖金我也要到手！

column2:
Ken, after one interview, they offered me the job! It happened so quick. No questions about my work or skills, they asked one question, "When can you start?" 

I'm going to make double what I make here.  You should come with me. There's a referral bonus if we can get more Murray employees to jump ship.
column3:
Ken，我才面试了一次，他们就给我发了offer！太快了，甚至没问我的工作经验或技能，只问了'你什么时候能来？'

我在那里拿到的是现在工资的两倍。你也过来吧！如果还能拉更多默里的员工一起跳槽，还有推荐奖金拿。

column2: Lee, the projector is down again in the theater. I swear this stupid show is cursed. What was Edwin thinking, making this kid's thing? Plus those things just creep me out.
column3: Lee，剧场的投影机又坏了。我说真的，这鸟节目真被诅咒了。埃德温到底怎么想的，做这么个小孩子的东西？这些玩意儿让人看着都发怵。
定位器
真喜欢那个售票亭！
邮件—8月3日
主入口
主办公室

column2: Me and Stan are out of here. It's time to jump ship before things get ugly. I have a bunch of Fiona's character patterns and Stan is taking what he can. Join us. With everything we know about the restaurant project, we can start our own machine shop.
column3: 我和Stan要走了。趁事情恶化前赶紧脱身。我拿了好多菲奥娜的角色设计，Stan也拿了自己能拿的。一起吧！凭咱们对那个餐厅项目的了解，足够开自家机修厂了。
继续前进！

column2: Mr. Murray. Bob in marketing had an amazing idea. Costumes are great for sports teams and high school pep rallys. We could almost double our sales output if we contacted schools. I will await your reply.
column3: 默里先生，市场部的Bob想到了个绝妙点子！那些套装在体育队和高中集会上很受欢迎。如果我们联系学校，销售额说不定能翻一倍。我等您的回复。

column2: My weekend vacation request was refused. I quit! Tell Jake I'll be back for my things on Monday.
column3: 我的周末休假申请居然被拒了。我不干了！告诉Jake我周一回去拿东西。
夜班

column2: No. Not for sports use. and NOT for personal use either... Sports never did anything good for me, so I'm not doing anything good for sports
column3: 不。不许用于体育活动，更不能私人用……体育这玩意儿从来没让我捞着什么好事，所以我也懒得管体育的事儿。

column2: None of this makes sense. Mr. Murray told us to trash all the old equipment in the wood shop. Then Stevenson gets a purchase order for the exact same stuff we're throwing out and told to install it upstairs. The old stuff is all perfectly functional. It's a waste of money.  So, Stevenson asks him about it and gets fired. He has to be out by the end of the day. My advice is keep your mouth shut. Don't even think about it. Just clear out the tunnels.
column3: 这事儿怎么想都不对劲。默里让我们把车间所有旧设备全扔了，结果Stevenson又接到一个采购单，买的全是那些我们刚扔的东西，还要求装去楼上。那些设备明明还好好的，纯属浪费钱。Stevenson去质问，居然被炒了，今天就得收拾走人。我的建议，闭嘴，别多事，赶紧把隧道整理出来。

column2: Obviously, we’ll have to move Bev’s party to the breakroom in the main hallway. Mr. Murray has given me permission to change the code to 49762. - Milton
column3: 很明显，我们得把贝芙的聚会挪到主走廊的休息室。默里先生已经允许我把门禁码改成49762。—米尔顿

column2: Okay everyone, that is quite enough. No more changes to the keycode please. - Milton
column3: 好了，大家，够了。请别再改门禁密码了。—米尔顿
原始设计
天际之外
请批示
电力
投影仪故障

column2: Ralph went to the hospital last night. That suit is going to be the death of one of us. One more injury and I'm out of here. I mean it this time.
column3: 拉尔夫昨晚进了医院。那身套装迟早要害死我们其中一个。要是再出一次事故，我就真的不干了，这次我是说真的。

column2: Same dialogue as original dispatch request... Got the cameras fixed
column3: 跟原始派工请求说的一样……摄像头修好了

column2: Shawn, I found out why they closed it down. There's something below us. I've trapped it behind the carousel for now, but I don't know how long that can hold it. I've programmed the monitors to give you the code.  I gotta go. I'll mail you later.
column3: 肖恩，我搞清楚他们为什么把那里封了。下面有个东西。我现在暂时把它困在旋转木马后面了，但不知道能撑多久。我已经让监控给你显示密码。我得赶紧走了，回头联系你。
好无聊啊！
拼写检查
拼写没问题！
弹簧锁机制
员工联系方式

column2: That sounds great! I’m going to change the last two digits to Bev’s age. Justice for Bev! - Penny
column3: 太好了！我打算把最后两位改成贝芙的年龄。为贝芙讨个公道！—佩妮
剧场
剧场—有人看见加里了吗？
剧场—又有人受伤？

column2: There you have it. Just don't use the code unless it's a matter of life or death! Have mercy on our souls if that thing ever gets out.
column3: 就这样。除非性命攸关，否则不要用这个密码！要是那玩意儿真的跑出来了，大家自求多福吧。

column2: This one of a kind ticket booth plays music and it collects tickets. It can hold signs for advertising or directions with its many arms.  Additional swings can be attached and make it a fun ride (We'll throw the swings in for free as a bonus).
column3: 这个独一无二的售票亭能放音乐还能验票。它有许多机械臂，可以举着广告牌或指示牌。还能加上秋千，变成一个好玩的游乐设施(秋千我们免费赠送)。

column2: To all Admin staff members. Mr. Murray’s party has been canceled, due to the recent tragic events. Please do not enter the conference room until further notice. - Milton
column3: 致全体行政人员：默里先生的派对因为近期悲剧事件被取消。请大家暂时不要进入会议室，等候通知。—米尔顿

column2: To all employees, Mr. Murray has taken over conference room 1 for a surprise birthday party for his son. The old keycode will not work anymore, so please stop trying 53782. It’s getting annoying. - Milton
column3: 致全体员工：默里先生已经占用1号会议室，给他儿子准备惊喜生日派对。原来的门禁码已经失效了，所以请别再输53782了，大家都快被烦死了。—米尔顿
假期

column2: Wait. What about Bev’s birthday party? That was supposed to be this Saturday. She turned 50 yesterday, and you're only 50 once! - Amy
column3: 等等，那贝芙的生日派对呢？那不是定在这个周六吗？她昨天刚满五十岁，这一辈子就这一次啊！—艾米
浪费钱

column2: We are almost there. I need the rest of the Murray staff contact info. The sooner the better. You get that for me, and I can sweeten the deal. How would you like to manage one of the new franchise locations? - W.A.
column3: 我们快完成了。我还需要剩下的默里部门员工联系方式，越快越好。你要是帮我搞定，我可以让条件更优厚。想不想去管理一家新开的特许分店？—W.A.
我们得走了

column2: Well, if you’re going to do that, I’m going to change the first two digits to 29. It’s my favorite number, so don’t change it! - Wally
column3: 那好，如果你真要这么搞，我就把前两位密码改为29。那是我最喜欢的数字，可千万别给我改！—沃利
你一整天都得站的地方

column2:
Why are we turning down work? The floats have been doing really well. Ed's modular system is groundbreaking. And now he wants to shut the whole thing down? He just sits in his office talking to that thing. I have no clue what to do. 
- Barbara
column3:
